ibmRIFFilterInBridgeMask.name: ibmRIFFilterInBridgeMask
ibmRIFFilterInBridgeMask.description: Mask to allow ibmRIFFilterInBridgeNumber to be used as a range of values.

ibmRIFFilterInRouteDesignator.name: ibmRIFFilterInRouteDesignator
ibmRIFFilterInRouteDesignator.description: Indicates which route designators in the routing information field are to be used for filtering.

ibmRIFFilterOutTable.name: ibmRIFFilterOutTable
ibmRIFFilterOutTable.description: Table of routing information field filtering information for outgoing frames.

ibmRIFFilterOutEntry.name: ibmRIFFilterOutEntry
ibmRIFFilterOutEntry.description: Filtering information for a single routing information field on a single interface.

ibmRIFFilterOutIfIndex.name: ibmRIFFilterOutIfIndex
ibmRIFFilterOutIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ibmRIFFilterOutRingNumber.name: ibmRIFFilterOutRingNumber
ibmRIFFilterOutRingNumber.description: Indicates which ring number to filter.

ibmRIFFilterOutRingMask.name: ibmRIFFilterOutRingMask
ibmRIFFilterOutRingMask.description: Mask to allow ibmRIFFilterOutRingNumber to be used as a range of values.

ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeNumber.name: ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeNumber
ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeNumber.description: Indicates which bridge number to filter.

ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeMask.name: ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeMask
ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeMask.description: Mask to allow ibmRIFFilterOutBridgeNumber to be used as a range of values.

ibmRIFFilterOutRouteDesignator.name: ibmRIFFilterOutRouteDesignator
ibmRIFFilterOutRouteDesignator.description: Indicates which route designators in the routing information field are to be used for filtering.

ibmfrDlcmiTable.name: ibmfrDlcmiTable
ibmfrDlcmiTable.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Annex D
ibmfrDlcmiTable.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface corresponding to any given ifEntry.

ibmfrDlcmiEntry.name: ibmfrDlcmiEntry
ibmfrDlcmiEntry.description: The Parameters for the Data Link Connection Management Interface.

ibmfrDlcmiIfIndex.name: ibmfrDlcmiIfIndex
ibmfrDlcmiIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the corresponding ifEn- try.

ibmfrDlcmiState.name: ibmfrDlcmiState
ibmfrDlcmiState.description: This variable states which Data Link Connec- tion Management scheme is active (and by impli- cation, what DLCI it uses) on the Frame Relay interface.

ibmfrDlcmiAddress.name: ibmfrDlcmiAddress
ibmfrDlcmiAddress.description: This variable states which address format is in use on the Frame Relay interface.

ibmfrDlcmiAddressLen.name: ibmfrDlcmiAddressLen
ibmfrDlcmiAddressLen.description: This variable states which address length in octets. In the case of Q922 format, the length indicates the entire length of the address in- cluding the control portion.

ibmfrDlcmiPollingInterval.name: ibmfrDlcmiPollingInterval
ibmfrDlcmiPollingInterval.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.7 Timer T391.
ibmfrDlcmiPollingInterval.description: This is the number of seconds between succes- sive status enquiry messages.

ibmfrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.name: ibmfrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval
ibmfrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.7 Counter N391.
ibmfrDlcmiFullEnquiryInterval.description: Number of status enquiry intervals that pass before issuance of a full status enquiry mes- sage.

ibmfrDlcmiErrorThreshold.name: ibmfrDlcmiErrorThreshold
ibmfrDlcmiErrorThreshold.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.5.1 Counter N392.
ibmfrDlcmiErrorThreshold.description: This is the maximum number of unanswered Status Enquiries the equipment shall accept be- fore declaring the interface down.

ibmfrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.name: ibmfrDlcmiMonitoredEvents
ibmfrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section D.5.2 Counter T393.
ibmfrDlcmiMonitoredEvents.description: This is the maximum number of responses to FULL STATUS or LINK INTEGERITY VERIFICATION messages missed before the device will mark the interface down.

ibmfrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.name: ibmfrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs
ibmfrDlcmiMaxSupportedVCs.description: The maximum number of Virtual Circuits allowed for this interface. Usually dictated by the Frame Relay network. In response to a SET, if a value less than zero or higher than the agent's maximal capability is configured, the agent should respond bad- Value

ibmfrDlcmiMulticast.name: ibmfrDlcmiMulticast
ibmfrDlcmiMulticast.description: This indicates whether the Frame Relay provid- er offers a Multicast Service.

ibmfrCircuitTable.name: ibmfrCircuitTable
ibmfrCircuitTable.description: A table containing information about specific Data Link Connection Identifiers and corresponding virtual circuits.

ibmfrCircuitEntry.name: ibmfrCircuitEntry
ibmfrCircuitEntry.description: The information regarding a single Data Link Connection Identifier.

ibmfrCircuitIfIndex.name: ibmfrCircuitIfIndex
ibmfrCircuitIfIndex.description: The ifIndex Value of the ifEntry this virtual circuit is layered onto.

ibmfrCircuitDlci.name: ibmfrCircuitDlci
ibmfrCircuitDlci.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.6
ibmfrCircuitDlci.description: The Data Link Connection Identifier for this virtual circuit.

ibmfrCircuitState.name: ibmfrCircuitState
ibmfrCircuitState.description: Indicates whether the particular virtual cir- cuit is operational. In the absence of a Data Link Connection Management Interface, virtual circuit entries (rows) may be created by set- ting virtual circuit state to active, or delet- ed by changing Circuit state to deleted. Whether or not the row actually disappears is let to the implementation, so this object may actually read as 'invalid' for some arbitrary length of time. It is also legal to set the state of a virtual circuit to inactive to tem- porarily disable a given circuit.

ibmfrCircuitReceivedFECNs.name: ibmfrCircuitReceivedFECNs
ibmfrCircuitReceivedFECNs.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.3
ibmfrCircuitReceivedFECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating forward congestion since the virtual circuit was created.

ibmfrCircuitReceivedBECNs.name: ibmfrCircuitReceivedBECNs
ibmfrCircuitReceivedBECNs.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.618-1991, Section 3.3.4
ibmfrCircuitReceivedBECNs.description: Number of frames received from the network in- dicating backward congestion since the virtual circuit was created.

ibmfrCircuitSentFrames.name: ibmfrCircuitSentFrames
ibmfrCircuitSentFrames.description: The number of frames sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

ibmfrCircuitSentOctets.name: ibmfrCircuitSentOctets
ibmfrCircuitSentOctets.description: The number of octets sent from this virtual circuit since it was created.

ibmfrCircuitReceivedFrames.name: ibmfrCircuitReceivedFrames
ibmfrCircuitReceivedFrames.description: Number of frames received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

ibmfrCircuitReceivedOctets.name: ibmfrCircuitReceivedOctets
ibmfrCircuitReceivedOctets.description: Number of octets received over this virtual circuit since it was created.

ibmfrCircuitCreationTime.name: ibmfrCircuitCreationTime
ibmfrCircuitCreationTime.description: The time when this virtual circuit was created, whether by the Data Link Connection Management Interface or by a SetRequest. The time value is relative to other times on this interface only.

ibmfrCircuitLastTimeChange.name: ibmfrCircuitLastTimeChange
ibmfrCircuitLastTimeChange.description: The time when last there was a change in the virtual circuit state. The time value is relative to other times on this interface only.

ibmfrCircuitCommittedBurst.name: ibmfrCircuitCommittedBurst
ibmfrCircuitCommittedBurst.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section 6.5.19
ibmfrCircuitCommittedBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of data, in bits, that the network agrees to transfer under normal conditions, during the measurement interval.

ibmfrCircuitExcessBurst.name: ibmfrCircuitExcessBurst
ibmfrCircuitExcessBurst.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section 6.5.19
ibmfrCircuitExcessBurst.description: This variable indicates the maximum amount of uncommitted data bits that the network will at- tempt to deliver over the measurement interval. By default, if not configured when creating the entry, the Excess Information Burst Size is set to the value of ifSpeed.

ibmfrCircuitThroughput.name: ibmfrCircuitThroughput
ibmfrCircuitThroughput.reference: Draft American National Standard T1.617-1991, Section 6.5.19
ibmfrCircuitThroughput.description: Throughput is the average number of 'Frame Re- lay Information Field' bits transferred per second across a user network interface in one direction, measured over the measurement inter- val. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both non-zero, the measurement interval T=ibmfrCircuitCommittedBurst/ibmfrCircuitThroughput. If the configured committed burst rate and throughput are both zero, the measurement in- terval T=ibmfrCircuitExcessBurst/ifSpeed.

ibmfrErrTable.name: ibmfrErrTable
ibmfrErrTable.description: A table containing information about Errors on the Frame Relay interface.

ibmfrErrEntry.name: ibmfrErrEntry
ibmfrErrEntry.description: The error information for a single frame relay interface.

ibmfrErrIfIndex.name: ibmfrErrIfIndex
ibmfrErrIfIndex.description: The ifIndex Value of the corresponding ifEn- try.

ibmfrErrType.name: ibmfrErrType
ibmfrErrType.description: The type of error that was last seen on this interface.

ibmfrErrData.name: ibmfrErrData
ibmfrErrData.description: An octet string containing as much of the er- ror packet as possible. As a minimum, it must contain the Q.922 Address or as much as was delivered. It is desirable to include all in- formation up to the PDU.

ibmfrErrTime.name: ibmfrErrTime
ibmfrErrTime.description: The time at which the error was detected. The time value is relative to other times on this interface only.

ibmdlsVirtualRingSegmentNumber.name: ibmdlsVirtualRingSegmentNumber
ibmdlsVirtualRingSegmentNumber.description: The token ring segment number used in all frames passed to or from the IBM 6611 Data Link Switching function.

ibmdlsFrameFilterType.name: ibmdlsFrameFilterType
ibmdlsFrameFilterType.description: The type of SNA filtering applied using the ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterTable and ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterTable. If this field = permit(2), then all filters defined for SNA use the action of permitting frames to be forwarded if they meet the criteria given by the source and destination address values. If this field = deny(1), then all filters defined for SNA use the action of denying frames to be forwarded if they meet the criteria given by the source and destination address values.

ibmdlsNameFilterType.name: ibmdlsNameFilterType
ibmdlsNameFilterType.description: The type of NetBIOS filtering applied using the ibmdlsLocalNameFilterTable and ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterTable. If this field = permit(2), then all filters defined for NetBIOS use the action of permitting frames to be forwarded if they meet the criteria given by the source and destination address values. If this field = deny(1), then all filters defined for NetBIOS use the action of denying frames to be forwarded if they meet the criteria given by the source and destination address values.

ibmdlsRouterTable.name: ibmdlsRouterTable
ibmdlsRouterTable.description: A table of information regarding all routers participating in Data Link Switching.

ibmdlsRouterEntry.name: ibmdlsRouterEntry
ibmdlsRouterEntry.description: Information for a single participating router.

ibmdlsRouterAddress.name: ibmdlsRouterAddress
ibmdlsRouterAddress.description: The IP address of the router participating in Data Link Switching.

ibmdlsRouterStatus.name: ibmdlsRouterStatus
ibmdlsRouterStatus.description: The current state of the remote connection

ibmdlsRouterDefinedBy.name: ibmdlsRouterDefinedBy
ibmdlsRouterDefinedBy.description: The origin of this entry. user(1) indicates that this router is defined via the Configuration Program. system(2) indicates that this router was defined automatically as a result of a connection request from another router.

ibmdlsRouterInFrames.name: ibmdlsRouterInFrames
ibmdlsRouterInFrames.description: Number of frames received from the partner router.

ibmdlsRouterOutFrames.name: ibmdlsRouterOutFrames
ibmdlsRouterOutFrames.description: Number of frames sent to the partner router.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterTable.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterTable
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterTable.description: The SNA local frame filter table. This table contains information regarding the filtering of SNA frames received from local LAN segments.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterEntry.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterEntry
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterEntry.description: Filter information for a MAC address source-destination pair.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterID.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterID
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterID.description: A unique identifier for this filter.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterSrcAddress.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterSrcAddress
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterSrcAddress.description: The source MAC address that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterSrcMask.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterSrcMask
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterSrcMask.description: A mask indicating the bits of the source address considered significant when using the filter. For every bit equal to one in the mask, the same bit in the source address is considered significant.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterDestAddress.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterDestAddress
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterDestAddress.description: The destination MAC address that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterDestMask.name: ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterDestMask
ibmdlsLocalFrameFilterDestMask.description: A mask indicating the bits of the destination address considered significant when using the filter. For every bit equal to one in the mask, the same bit in the destination address is considered significant.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterTable.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterTable
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterTable.description: The SNA remote frame filter table. This table contains information regarding the filtering of SNA frames received from other participating DLS routers.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterEntry.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterEntry
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterEntry.description: Filter information for a MAC address source-destination pair.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterID.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterID
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterID.description: A unique identifier for this filter.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterSrcAddress.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterSrcAddress
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterSrcAddress.description: The source MAC address that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterSrcMask.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterSrcMask
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterSrcMask.description: A mask indicating the bits of the source address considered significant when using the filter. For every bit equal to one in the mask, the same bit in the source address is considered significant.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterDestAddress.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterDestAddress
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterDestAddress.description: The destination MAC address that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterDestMask.name: ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterDestMask
ibmdlsRemoteFrameFilterDestMask.description: A mask indicating the bits of the destination address considered significant when using the filter. For every bit equal to one in the mask, the same bit in the destination address is considered significant.

ibmdlsLocalNameFilterTable.name: ibmdlsLocalNameFilterTable
ibmdlsLocalNameFilterTable.description: The NetBIOS local name filter table. This table contains information regarding the filtering of NetBIOS frames received from local LAN segments.

ibmdlsLocalNameFilterEntry.name: ibmdlsLocalNameFilterEntry
ibmdlsLocalNameFilterEntry.description: Filter information for a NetBIOS source-destination name pair.

ibmdlsLocalNameFilterID.name: ibmdlsLocalNameFilterID
ibmdlsLocalNameFilterID.description: A unique identifier for this filter.

ibmdlsLocalNameFilterSrcAddress.name: ibmdlsLocalNameFilterSrcAddress
ibmdlsLocalNameFilterSrcAddress.description: The source NetBIOS name that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsLocalNameFilterDestAddress.name: ibmdlsLocalNameFilterDestAddress
ibmdlsLocalNameFilterDestAddress.description: The destination NetBIOS name that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterTable.name: ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterTable
ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterTable.description: The NetBIOS name filter table. This table contains information regarding the filtering of NetBIOS frames received from other participating DLS routers.

ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterEntry.name: ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterEntry
ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterEntry.description: Filter information for a NetBIOS source-destination name pair.

ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterID.name: ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterID
ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterID.description: A unique identifier for this filter.

ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterSrcAddress.name: ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterSrcAddress
ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterSrcAddress.description: The source NetBIOS name that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterDestAddress.name: ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterDestAddress
ibmdlsRemoteNameFilterDestAddress.description: The destination NetBIOS name that this filter is applied to.

ibmdlsDefaultDestTable.name: ibmdlsDefaultDestTable
ibmdlsDefaultDestTable.description: Table of default routers for MAC addresses.

ibmdlsDefaultDestEntry.name: ibmdlsDefaultDestEntry
ibmdlsDefaultDestEntry.description: Mapping of a MAC address to a default router.

ibmdlsDefaultDestAddress.name: ibmdlsDefaultDestAddress
ibmdlsDefaultDestAddress.description: The destination address that this table entry applies to.

ibmdlsDefaultRouterAddress.name: ibmdlsDefaultRouterAddress
ibmdlsDefaultRouterAddress.description: The default router used for reaching the destination address in ibmdlsDefaultDestAddress.

ibmdlsDefaultNBDestTable.name: ibmdlsDefaultNBDestTable
ibmdlsDefaultNBDestTable.description: Table of default routers for NetBIOS names.

ibmdlsDefaultNBDestEntry.name: ibmdlsDefaultNBDestEntry
ibmdlsDefaultNBDestEntry.description: Mapping of a NetBIOS name to a default router.

ibmdlsDefaultNBDestName.name: ibmdlsDefaultNBDestName
ibmdlsDefaultNBDestName.description: The destination NetBIOS name that this table entry applies to.

ibmdlsDefaultNBRouterAddress.name: ibmdlsDefaultNBRouterAddress
ibmdlsDefaultNBRouterAddress.description: The default router used for reaching the destination name in ibmdlsDefaultNBDestName.

ibmdlsStationTable.name: ibmdlsStationTable
ibmdlsStationTable.description: Table of configuration information on SNA stations attached to this router.

ibmdlsStationEntry.name: ibmdlsStationEntry
ibmdlsStationEntry.description: Information on a single SNA station attached to this router.

ibmdlsStationIfIndex.name: ibmdlsStationIfIndex
ibmdlsStationIfIndex.description: The value of IfIndex for the port to which this station is attached.

ibmdlsStationAddress.name: ibmdlsStationAddress
ibmdlsStationAddress.description: The SDLC address of this station.

ibmdlsStationTransmitWindowCount.name: ibmdlsStationTransmitWindowCount
ibmdlsStationTransmitWindowCount.description: The number of SDLC information frames to send to this station before turning the line around to get a response.

ibmdlsStationRetransmitCount.name: ibmdlsStationRetransmitCount
ibmdlsStationRetransmitCount.description: The number of contiguous information frame bursts that will be transmitted to this station before declaring a permanent transmission error.

ibmdlsStationRetransmitThreshold.name: ibmdlsStationRetransmitThreshold
ibmdlsStationRetransmitThreshold.description: The number of information frame transmissions allowed as a percentage of total information frame transmissions. The specified rate is the maximum rate of retransmissions allowed above which an error log entry will be make.

ibmdlsStationForceDisconnectTimeout.name: ibmdlsStationForceDisconnectTimeout
ibmdlsStationForceDisconnectTimeout.description: The number of seconds that the IBM 6611 will wait after requesting a disconnect from the link (DISC) before forcing a disconnect.

ibmdlsStationMaxIfieldSize.name: ibmdlsStationMaxIfieldSize
ibmdlsStationMaxIfieldSize.description: The value in bytes of the maximum I-field size (a multiple of 256 plus 9).

ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollTimeout.name: ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollTimeout
ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollTimeout.description: The length of time (in tenths of seconds) that the primary station will wait for a response from the secondary station.

ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollCount.name: ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollCount
ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollCount.description: The number of times that the primary station will poll the secondary station unsuccessfully before marking the station as not working.

ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollThreshold.name: ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollThreshold
ibmdlsStationPrimaryRepollThreshold.description: The number of repolls as a percentage of the total polls sent to the secondary station. The specified percentage equals the maximum rate of repolls allowed, above which the IBM 6611 declares that a temporary error has occurred and logs an entry in the system error log.

ibmdlsStationPrimarySlowListTimeout.name: ibmdlsStationPrimarySlowListTimeout
ibmdlsStationPrimarySlowListTimeout.description: The number of seconds that the primary station will wait between polls to stations on the slow list.

ibmdlsStationSrcAddress.name: ibmdlsStationSrcAddress
ibmdlsStationSrcAddress.description: The token ring physical address used for this station.

ibmdlsStationDestAddress.name: ibmdlsStationDestAddress
ibmdlsStationDestAddress.description: The token ring physical address to which this station should be connected. If this information is not available the IBM 6611 Network Processor will return a length of zero for this object.

ibmdlsCirTable.name: ibmdlsCirTable
ibmdlsCirTable.description: Table of information on DLS circuits active on this router.

ibmdlsCirIfIndex.name: ibmdlsCirIfIndex
ibmdlsCirIfIndex.description: The value of IfIndex for the interface supporting this circuit.

ibmdlsCirSrcAddress.name: ibmdlsCirSrcAddress
ibmdlsCirSrcAddress.description: The MAC address of the source of this circuit.

ibmdlsCirSrcSap.name: ibmdlsCirSrcSap
ibmdlsCirSrcSap.description: The SAP identifier of the source of this circuit.

ibmdlsCirDestAddress.name: ibmdlsCirDestAddress
ibmdlsCirDestAddress.description: The MAC address of the destination of this circuit.

ibmdlsCirDestSap.name: ibmdlsCirDestSap
ibmdlsCirDestSap.description: The SAP identifier of the destination of this circuit.

ibmdlsCirPartnerRouterAddress.name: ibmdlsCirPartnerRouterAddress
ibmdlsCirPartnerRouterAddress.description: The IP address of the partner router used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkState.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkState
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkState.description: The state of the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkSubState.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkSubState
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkSubState.description: The sub-state of the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRouting.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRouting
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRouting.reference: IBM Token-ring Network: Architecture Reference (SC30-3374), see 'Routing Information Field'.
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRouting.description: The routing information field used by the local link portion of this circuit. The routing information field consists of a 2-byte routing control field and up to eight 2-byte route designators.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsSent.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsSent
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsSent.description: The number of test commands sent by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsFail.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsFail
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsFail.description: The number of test commands failed by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsRcv.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsRcv
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkTestCmdsRcv.description: The number of test commands received by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktSent.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktSent
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktSent.description: The number of sequenced data packets sent by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktResent.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktResent
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktResent.description: The number of sequenced data packets resent by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkMaxContResent.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkMaxContResent
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkMaxContResent.description: The maximum number of contiguous resendings by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktRcv.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktRcv
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkDataPktRcv.description: The number of sequenced data packets received by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkInvalidPktRcv.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkInvalidPktRcv
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkInvalidPktRcv.description: The number of invalid packets received by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkAdpRcvErr.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkAdpRcvErr
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkAdpRcvErr.description: The number of data-detected receive errors by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkAdpSendErr.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkAdpSendErr
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkAdpSendErr.description: The number of data-detected transmit errors by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRcvInactiveTimeouts.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRcvInactiveTimeouts
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkRcvInactiveTimeouts.description: The number of inactivity timeouts received by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdPollsSent.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdPollsSent
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdPollsSent.description: The number of command polls sent by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdRepollsSent.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdRepollsSent
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdRepollsSent.description: The number of command repolls sent by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdContRepolls.name: ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdContRepolls
ibmdlsCirLocalLinkCmdContRepolls.description: The number of continuous repolls sent by the local link station used by this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalAddress.name: ibmdlsCirLocalAddress
ibmdlsCirLocalAddress.description: The address (ibmdlsCirSrcAddress or ibmdlsCirDestAddress) that is local on this circuit.

ibmdlsCirLocalConnectionState.name: ibmdlsCirLocalConnectionState
ibmdlsCirLocalConnectionState.description: The state of the DLSw circuit connection based upon the progression of events as a logical link station and its associated DLSw connection is brought up or down.

ibmpppLinkControlTable.name: ibmpppLinkControlTable
ibmpppLinkControlTable.description: A table containing PPP-link specific control variables for this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppLinkControlIndex value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppLinkControlEntry.name: ibmpppLinkControlEntry
ibmpppLinkControlEntry.description: Management control information about a particular PPP Link.

ibmpppLinkControlIndex.name: ibmpppLinkControlIndex
ibmpppLinkControlIndex.description: A unique value for each PPP link. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is that identified by the same value of an ifIndex object instance. The value for each link must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ibmpppLinkCRCSize.name: ibmpppLinkCRCSize
ibmpppLinkCRCSize.description: Number of bits used in the CRC on this link. See section 3.1, 'Frame Check Sequence (FCS) Field' on page 5 of RFC 1171. Setting this object to a new value will have effect when this link is next restarted.

ibmpppLinkRestartTimerValue.name: ibmpppLinkRestartTimerValue
ibmpppLinkRestartTimerValue.description: The value used for the Restart Timer. It is in units of hundredths of a second. See section 4.3, 'Timers and Counters' on page 20 of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkMaxRestarts.name: ibmpppLinkMaxRestarts
ibmpppLinkMaxRestarts.description: The Max-Restarts parameter described in section 4.3, 'Timers and Counters' on page 20 of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkLocalMRU.name: ibmpppLinkLocalMRU
ibmpppLinkLocalMRU.description: The MRU (Maximum Receive Unit) of this node on the link. See section 2.1, page 2, 'Maximum Receive Unit' of RFC 1172. Changing this object will have effect when the link is next restarted.

ibmpppLinkRemoteMRU.name: ibmpppLinkRemoteMRU
ibmpppLinkRemoteMRU.description: What this node believes is the MRU for the node on the other end of the link. See section 2.1, page 2, 'Maximum Receive Unit' of RFC 1172. Changing this object will immediately cause the local node to use the new MRU when transmitting packets. If this number is increased, then the sender MAY elect to use the new MRU. If the MRU is decreased then the sender MUST use the new MRU.

ibmpppLinkLocalACCMap.name: ibmpppLinkLocalACCMap
ibmpppLinkLocalACCMap.description: The (ACC) Asynchronous-Control-Character-Map for this node. This is the ACC Map that the node on the other end of the link will use when building a packet to send to this node. See section 2.2, page 3, 'Async-Control- Character-Map' of RFC 1172. The IBM 6611 Network Processor always provides a value of zero for this object.

ibmpppLinkRemoteACCMap.name: ibmpppLinkRemoteACCMap
ibmpppLinkRemoteACCMap.description: The (ACC) Asynchronous-Control-Character-Map that this node uses when building a packet to send to the node on the other end of the link. See section 2.2, page 3, 'Async-Control-Character-Map' of RFC 1172. The IBM 6611 Network Processor always provides a value of zero for this object.

ibmpppLinkMagicLoopCount.name: ibmpppLinkMagicLoopCount
ibmpppLinkMagicLoopCount.description: The number of times that this node will do a Magic Number Configuration before deciding that the link is looped back. 0 indicates that the node does not do Magic Number Configuration. -1 indicates that it tries forever. Changing this object takes effect the next time that the link is restarted.

ibmpppLinkCommand.name: ibmpppLinkCommand
ibmpppLinkCommand.description: See section 4.14 on page 13 of RFC 1171. Reading from this variable will return no-op(1). The IBM 6611 Network Processor always provides a value of no-op(1) for this object.

ibmpppLinkStatusTable.name: ibmpppLinkStatusTable
ibmpppLinkStatusTable.description: A table containing PPP-link status specific information for this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppLinkStatusIndex value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppLinkStatusEntry.name: ibmpppLinkStatusEntry
ibmpppLinkStatusEntry.description: Status information about a particular PPP Link.

ibmpppLinkStatusIndex.name: ibmpppLinkStatusIndex
ibmpppLinkStatusIndex.description: A unique value for each PPP link. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is that identified by the same value of an ifIndex object instance. The value for each link must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ibmpppLinkVersion.name: ibmpppLinkVersion
ibmpppLinkVersion.description: The version of LCP that is being run over this link (per RFC 1171). This value currently must be 1.

ibmpppLinkCurrentState.name: ibmpppLinkCurrentState
ibmpppLinkCurrentState.description: The current state of the link automaton. See section 4.1.3. 'State Transition Table' on page 13 of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkPreviousState.name: ibmpppLinkPreviousState
ibmpppLinkPreviousState.description: The immediately previous state of the link automaton. See section 4.1.3. 'State Transition Table' on page 13 of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkChangeTime.name: ibmpppLinkChangeTime
ibmpppLinkChangeTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the state of the link automaton last changed.

ibmpppLinkMagicNumber.name: ibmpppLinkMagicNumber
ibmpppLinkMagicNumber.description: This node's Magic Number. See section 2.4, page 7, 'Magic Number' of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkLocalQualityPeriod.name: ibmpppLinkLocalQualityPeriod
ibmpppLinkLocalQualityPeriod.description: This is the maximum interval at which this node will transmit Link-Quality-Report Packets. See section 2.5, on page 10 of RFC 1172. This object is in units of microseconds.

ibmpppLinkRemoteQualityPeriod.name: ibmpppLinkRemoteQualityPeriod
ibmpppLinkRemoteQualityPeriod.description: This is the maximum interval at which this node expects that the other node will transmit Link-Quality-Report Packets. See section 2.5, on page 10 of RFC 1172. This object is in units of microseconds.

ibmpppLinkProtocolCompression.name: ibmpppLinkProtocolCompression
ibmpppLinkProtocolCompression.description: Indicates the Protocol compression that has been configured on the link. Receive-only(1) indicates that this node can receive compressed packets but won't send them. Send-only(2) indicates that this node will send compressed packets but can not receive them. Receive-and-send(3) indicates that the node will send and can receive compressed packets. None(4) indicates that this node will neither send nor receive compressed packets. See section 2.6, on page 11 of RFC 1172. The IBM 6611 Network Processor always provides a value of none(4) for this object.

ibmpppLinkACCompression.name: ibmpppLinkACCompression
ibmpppLinkACCompression.description: Indicates the Address/Control Field compression that has been configured on the link. Receive-only(1) indicates that this node can receive compressed packets but won't send them. Send-only(2) indicates that this node will send compressed packets but can not receive them. Receive-and- send(3) indicates that the node will send and can receive compressed packets. None(4) indicates that this node will neither send nor receive compressed packets. See section 2.7, on page 13 of RFC 1172. The IBM 6611 Network Processor always provides a value of none(4) for this object.

ibmpppLinkMeasurementsValid.name: ibmpppLinkMeasurementsValid
ibmpppLinkMeasurementsValid.description: The current value of the Measurements-Valid state variable used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkQuality.name: ibmpppLinkQuality
ibmpppLinkQuality.description: The current quality of the link as declared by the nodes Link-Quality Management modules. No effort is made to define good or bad, nor the policy used to determine it.

ibmpppLinkPhysical.name: ibmpppLinkPhysical
ibmpppLinkPhysical.description: A reference to MIB definitions specific to the particular physical interface type (e.g. T1) being used by the PPP Link. If the agent is unable to obtain this information, the value of this object will be set to the OBJECT IDENTIFIER { 0 0 }, which is a syntatically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

ibmpppLinkErrorsTable.name: ibmpppLinkErrorsTable
ibmpppLinkErrorsTable.description: A table containing PPP-link specific statistical information for this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppLinkErrorsIndex value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppLinkErrorsEntry.name: ibmpppLinkErrorsEntry
ibmpppLinkErrorsEntry.description: Error information about a particular PPP Link.

ibmpppLinkErrorsIndex.name: ibmpppLinkErrorsIndex
ibmpppLinkErrorsIndex.description: A unique value for each PPP link. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is that identified by the same value of an ifIndex object instance. The value for each link must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ibmpppLinkBadAddresses.name: ibmpppLinkBadAddresses
ibmpppLinkBadAddresses.description: The number of packets received with an incorrect Address Field. See section 3.1, Page 5, 'Address Field' of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkLastBadAddress.name: ibmpppLinkLastBadAddress
ibmpppLinkLastBadAddress.description: The most recent incorrect address received on this link.

ibmpppLinkBadControls.name: ibmpppLinkBadControls
ibmpppLinkBadControls.description: The number of packets received on this link with an incorrect Control Field. See Section 3.1, Page 5, 'Flag Sequence' of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkLastBadControl.name: ibmpppLinkLastBadControl
ibmpppLinkLastBadControl.description: The most recent incorrect Control Field received on this link.

ibmpppLinkLastUnknownProtocol.name: ibmpppLinkLastUnknownProtocol
ibmpppLinkLastUnknownProtocol.description: The most recently received unknown Protocol. An unknown Protocol is one which has a well-formed Protocol number, but which the PPP implementation does not know how to handle.

ibmpppLinkInvalidProtocols.name: ibmpppLinkInvalidProtocols
ibmpppLinkInvalidProtocols.description: The number of times that a packet has been received with an invalid Protocol specified in the Protocol Field. An invalid Protocol is one which does not conform to the requirements of section 3.1, page 5 of RFC 1171.

ibmpppLinkLastInvalidProtocol.name: ibmpppLinkLastInvalidProtocol
ibmpppLinkLastInvalidProtocol.description: The most recently received invalid Protocol.

ibmpppLinkPacketTooLongs.name: ibmpppLinkPacketTooLongs
ibmpppLinkPacketTooLongs.description: The number of received packets that have been discarded because their length exceeded the MRU.

ibmpppLinkBadCRCs.name: ibmpppLinkBadCRCs
ibmpppLinkBadCRCs.description: The number of received packets that have been discarded due to having an incorrect CRC.

ibmpppLinkConfigTimeouts.name: ibmpppLinkConfigTimeouts
ibmpppLinkConfigTimeouts.description: The number of Configure Request packets that have timed out.

ibmpppLinkTerminateTimeouts.name: ibmpppLinkTerminateTimeouts
ibmpppLinkTerminateTimeouts.description: The number of Terminate Request packets that have timed out.

ibmpppLinkQualityTable.name: ibmpppLinkQualityTable
ibmpppLinkQualityTable.description: A table containing PPP-link specific statistical information for this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppLinkQualityIndex value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppLinkQualityEntry.name: ibmpppLinkQualityEntry
ibmpppLinkQualityEntry.description: Link Quality Management information about a particular PPP Link.

ibmpppLinkQualityIndex.name: ibmpppLinkQualityIndex
ibmpppLinkQualityIndex.description: A unique value for each PPP link. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is that identified by the same value of an ifIndex object instance. The value for each link must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization.

ibmpppLinkInTxLQRs.name: ibmpppLinkInTxLQRs
ibmpppLinkInTxLQRs.description: The current value of In-Tx-LQRs used in Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkInTxPackets.name: ibmpppLinkInTxPackets
ibmpppLinkInTxPackets.description: The current value of the In-Tx-Packets counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkLastOutTxPackets.name: ibmpppLinkLastOutTxPackets
ibmpppLinkLastOutTxPackets.description: The current value of the Last-Out-Tx-Packets-Ctr counter used bu Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkInTxOctets.name: ibmpppLinkInTxOctets
ibmpppLinkInTxOctets.description: The current value of the In-Tx-Octets counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkLastOutTxOctets.name: ibmpppLinkLastOutTxOctets
ibmpppLinkLastOutTxOctets.description: The current value of the Last-Out-Tx-Octets-Counter counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkInRxPackets.name: ibmpppLinkInRxPackets
ibmpppLinkInRxPackets.description: The current value of the In-Rx-Packets counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkLastInRxPackets.name: ibmpppLinkLastInRxPackets
ibmpppLinkLastInRxPackets.description: The current value of the Last-In-Rx-Packets-Ctr counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkInRxOctets.name: ibmpppLinkInRxOctets
ibmpppLinkInRxOctets.description: The current value of the In-Rx-Octets counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppLinkLastInRxOctets.name: ibmpppLinkLastInRxOctets
ibmpppLinkLastInRxOctets.description: The current value of the Last-In-Rx-Octets-Ctr counter used for Link-Quality Management. See section 3.5, page 19, of RFC 1172.

ibmpppIPTable.name: ibmpppIPTable
ibmpppIPTable.description: A table containing specific information for the running of the IP over PPP in this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppIPLinkNumber value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppIPEntry.name: ibmpppIPEntry
ibmpppIPEntry.description: All information pertinant to running the IP over a single PPP link.

ibmpppIPLinkNumber.name: ibmpppIPLinkNumber
ibmpppIPLinkNumber.description: The value of ibmpppLinkIndex for the link over which this instance of the IP is being run.

ibmpppIPRejects.name: ibmpppIPRejects
ibmpppIPRejects.description: The number of Protocol Reject Messages received when attempting to send an IP packet over the link identified by ibmpppIPLinkNumber.

ibmpppIPInPackets.name: ibmpppIPInPackets
ibmpppIPInPackets.description: The number of IP packets received on the link identified by ibmpppIPLinkNumber.

ibmpppIPInOctets.name: ibmpppIPInOctets
ibmpppIPInOctets.description: The number of octets received in IP packets received on the link identified by ibmpppIPLinkNumber. Only octets in the PPP Information Field are counted. Octets inserted for transparency are not counted. Padding octets are not counted.

ibmpppIPOutPackets.name: ibmpppIPOutPackets
ibmpppIPOutPackets.description: The number of IP packets sent on the link identified by ibmpppIPLinkNumber.

ibmpppIPOutOctets.name: ibmpppIPOutOctets
ibmpppIPOutOctets.description: The number of octets all in IP Packets sent on the link identified by ibmpppIPLinkNumber. Only octets in the PPP Information Field are counted. Octets inserted for transparency are not counted. Padding octets are not counted.

ibmpppIPCPTable.name: ibmpppIPCPTable
ibmpppIPCPTable.description: A table containing specific information for the running of the IPCP over PPP in this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppIPCPEntry.name: ibmpppIPCPEntry
ibmpppIPCPEntry.description: All information pertinant to running the IPCP over a single PPP link.

ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber.name: ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber
ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber.description: The value of ibmpppLinkIndex for the link over which this instance of the IPCP is being run.

ibmpppIPCPRejects.name: ibmpppIPCPRejects
ibmpppIPCPRejects.description: The number of Protocol Reject Messages received when attempting to send an IPCP Packet over the link identified by ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber.

ibmpppIPCPInPackets.name: ibmpppIPCPInPackets
ibmpppIPCPInPackets.description: The number of IPCP packets received on the link identified by ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber.

ibmpppIPCPInOctets.name: ibmpppIPCPInOctets
ibmpppIPCPInOctets.description: The number of octets received in IPCP packets received on the link identified by ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber. Only octets in the PPP Information Field are counted. Octets inserted for transparency are not counted. Padding octets are not counted.

ibmpppIPCPOutPackets.name: ibmpppIPCPOutPackets
ibmpppIPCPOutPackets.description: The number of IPCP packets sent on the link identified by ibmpppIPLinkNumber.

ibmpppIPCPOutOctets.name: ibmpppIPCPOutOctets
ibmpppIPCPOutOctets.description: The number of octets all in IPCP packets sent on the link identified by ibmpppIPCPLinkNumber. Only octets in the PPP Information Field are counted. Octets inserted for transparency are not counted. Padding octets are not counted.

ibmpppIPCPCompressionType.name: ibmpppIPCPCompressionType
ibmpppIPCPCompressionType.description: The compression type used on this link as defined in section 5.2 of RFC 1172. The numerical values that this object can be are the same as the numerical values that are included in the IPCP compression option configuration packets. The IBM 6611 Network Processor always provides a value of none(1) for this object.

ibmpppLCPTable.name: ibmpppLCPTable
ibmpppLCPTable.description: A table containing specific information for the running of LCP over PPP in this managed object. An entry in this table is uniquely identified by the ibmpppLCPLinkNumber value comprised by said entry.

ibmpppLCPEntry.name: ibmpppLCPEntry
ibmpppLCPEntry.description: All information pertinant to running LCP over a single PPP link.

ibmpppLCPLinkNumber.name: ibmpppLCPLinkNumber
ibmpppLCPLinkNumber.description: The value of ibmpppLinkIndex for the link over which this instance of LCP is being run.

ibmpppLCPRejects.name: ibmpppLCPRejects
ibmpppLCPRejects.description: The number of Protocol Reject Messages received when attempting to send an LCP packet over the link identified by ibmpppLCPLinkNumber. This really ought not to happen.

ibmpppLCPInPackets.name: ibmpppLCPInPackets
ibmpppLCPInPackets.description: The number of LCP packets received on the link identified by ibmpppLCPLinkNumber.

ibmpppLCPInOctets.name: ibmpppLCPInOctets
ibmpppLCPInOctets.description: The number of octets received in LCP packets received on the link identified by ibmpppLCPLinkNumber. Only octets in the PPP Information Field are counted. Octets inserted for transparency are not counted. Padding octets are not counted.

ibmpppLCPOutPackets.name: ibmpppLCPOutPackets
ibmpppLCPOutPackets.description: The number of LCP packets sent on the link identified by ibmpppLCPLinkNumber.

ibmpppLCPOutOctets.name: ibmpppLCPOutOctets
ibmpppLCPOutOctets.description: The number of octets all in LCP packets sent on the link identified by ibmpppLCPLinkNumber. Only octets in the PPP Information Field are counted. Octets inserted for transparency are not counted. Padding octets are not counted.

ibmpppLCPOutCRs.name: ibmpppLCPOutCRs
ibmpppLCPOutCRs.description: Number of Configuration Request packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInCRs.name: ibmpppLCPInCRs
ibmpppLCPInCRs.description: Number of Configuration Request packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutCAs.name: ibmpppLCPOutCAs
ibmpppLCPOutCAs.description: Number of Configuration Acknowledge packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInCAs.name: ibmpppLCPInCAs
ibmpppLCPInCAs.description: Number of Configuration Acknowledge packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutCNs.name: ibmpppLCPOutCNs
ibmpppLCPOutCNs.description: Number of Configuration NAK packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInCNs.name: ibmpppLCPInCNs
ibmpppLCPInCNs.description: Number of Configuration NAK packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutCRejs.name: ibmpppLCPOutCRejs
ibmpppLCPOutCRejs.description: Number of Configuration Reject packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInCRejs.name: ibmpppLCPInCRejs
ibmpppLCPInCRejs.description: Number of Configuration Reject packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutTRs.name: ibmpppLCPOutTRs
ibmpppLCPOutTRs.description: Number of Terminate Request packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInTRs.name: ibmpppLCPInTRs
ibmpppLCPInTRs.description: Number of Terminate Request packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutTAs.name: ibmpppLCPOutTAs
ibmpppLCPOutTAs.description: Number of Terminate Acknowledge packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInTAs.name: ibmpppLCPInTAs
ibmpppLCPInTAs.description: Number of Terminate Acknowledge packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutCodeRejs.name: ibmpppLCPOutCodeRejs
ibmpppLCPOutCodeRejs.description: Number of Code Reject packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInCodeRejs.name: ibmpppLCPInCodeRejs
ibmpppLCPInCodeRejs.description: Number of Code Reject packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutEchoReqs.name: ibmpppLCPOutEchoReqs
ibmpppLCPOutEchoReqs.description: Number of Echo Request packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInEchoReqs.name: ibmpppLCPInEchoReqs
ibmpppLCPInEchoReqs.description: Number of Echo Request packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutEchoReps.name: ibmpppLCPOutEchoReps
ibmpppLCPOutEchoReps.description: Number of Echo Reply packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInEchoReps.name: ibmpppLCPInEchoReps
ibmpppLCPInEchoReps.description: Number of Echo Reply packets received on this link.

ibmpppLCPOutDiscReqs.name: ibmpppLCPOutDiscReqs
ibmpppLCPOutDiscReqs.description: Number of Discard Request packets sent on this link.

ibmpppLCPInDiscReqs.name: ibmpppLCPInDiscReqs
ibmpppLCPInDiscReqs.description: Number of Discard Request packets received on this link.

ibmxnsidpForwarding.name: ibmxnsidpForwarding
ibmxnsidpForwarding.description: Indicates if this node is acting as an XNS router.

ibmxnsConfigTable.name: ibmxnsConfigTable
ibmxnsConfigTable.description: The table of XNS configuration information gathered on a per-interface basis.

ibmxnsConfigEntry.name: ibmxnsConfigEntry
ibmxnsConfigEntry.description: XNS configuration information for a single interface.

ibmxnsPortIfIndex.name: ibmxnsPortIfIndex
ibmxnsPortIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ibmxnsPortStatus.name: ibmxnsPortStatus
ibmxnsPortStatus.description: The status of the XNS protocol stack on this interface.

ibmxnsidpChecksum.name: ibmxnsidpChecksum
ibmxnsidpChecksum.description: Indicates the type of checksumming being done by IDP.

ibmxnsErrpActive.name: ibmxnsErrpActive
ibmxnsErrpActive.description: Indicates if this port is originating error protocol packets.

ibmxnsLoopbackActive.name: ibmxnsLoopbackActive
ibmxnsLoopbackActive.description: Indicates if this port will use the hardware to loopback locally addressed packets or return the packet to the system via a software loopback.

ibmxnsidpInReceives.name: ibmxnsidpInReceives
ibmxnsidpInReceives.description: Total number of IDP datagrams received.

ibmxnsidpBcastInReceives.name: ibmxnsidpBcastInReceives
ibmxnsidpBcastInReceives.description: Number of IDP broadcast datagrams received.

ibmxnsidpMcastInReceives.name: ibmxnsidpMcastInReceives
ibmxnsidpMcastInReceives.description: Number of IDP multicast datagrams received.

ibmxnsidpInDiscards.name: ibmxnsidpInDiscards
ibmxnsidpInDiscards.description: Number of incoming IDP datagrams discarded due to lack of resources.

ibmxnsidpOutRequests.name: ibmxnsidpOutRequests
ibmxnsidpOutRequests.description: Number of IDP datagrams generated by local IDP user protocols. This counter does not include any datagrams counted in ibmxnsidpForwDatagrams.

ibmxnsidpBcastOutRequests.name: ibmxnsidpBcastOutRequests
ibmxnsidpBcastOutRequests.description: Number of IDP broadcast datagrams generated by local IDP user protocols. This counter does not include any datagrams counted in ibmxnsidpForwDatagrams.

ibmxnsidpMcastOutRequests.name: ibmxnsidpMcastOutRequests
ibmxnsidpMcastOutRequests.description: Number of IDP multicast datagrams generated by local IDP user protocols. This counter does not include any datagrams counted in ibmxnsidpForwDatagrams.

ibmxnsidpForwDatagrams.name: ibmxnsidpForwDatagrams
ibmxnsidpForwDatagrams.description: Number of IDP datagrams for which an attempt was made to forward.

ibmxnsidpOutDiscards.name: ibmxnsidpOutDiscards
ibmxnsidpOutDiscards.description: Total number of outgoing IDP datagrams discarded.

ibmxnsidpOutNoRoutes.name: ibmxnsidpOutNoRoutes
ibmxnsidpOutNoRoutes.description: Number of outgoing IDP datagrams discarded because no route was available to the specified destination.

ibmxnsidpRoutingDiscards.name: ibmxnsidpRoutingDiscards
ibmxnsidpRoutingDiscards.description: Number of routing entries discarded even though they were valid.

ibmxnsidpZeroDirBcast.name: ibmxnsidpZeroDirBcast
ibmxnsidpZeroDirBcast.description: Number of IDP datagrams forwarded to the system due to zeronet broadcast.

ibmxnsidpTooSmall.name: ibmxnsidpTooSmall
ibmxnsidpTooSmall.description: Number of IDP datagrams with len < the size of an IDP header.

ibmxnsidpBadLen.name: ibmxnsidpBadLen
ibmxnsidpBadLen.description: Number of IDP datagrams with number of bytes in the packet less than the number of bytes specified in the IDP header field.

ibmxnsidpBadSum.name: ibmxnsidpBadSum
ibmxnsidpBadSum.description: Number of IDP datagrams with a bad checksum

ibmxnsidpBadTTL.name: ibmxnsidpBadTTL
ibmxnsidpBadTTL.description: Number of IDP datagrams with TTL value > IDP maximum hopcount of 16.

ibmxnsErrUnspec.name: ibmxnsErrUnspec
ibmxnsErrUnspec.description: Number of Error packets generated because an IDP datagram was dropped for unspecified reasons.

ibmxnsErrChecksum.name: ibmxnsErrChecksum
ibmxnsErrChecksum.description: Number of Error packets generated because an IDP datagram was dropped due a bad checksum.

ibmxnsErrUnreach.name: ibmxnsErrUnreach
ibmxnsErrUnreach.description: Number of Error packets generated because an IDP datagram was dropped due to an unreachable host.

ibmxnsErrTTLExpired.name: ibmxnsErrTTLExpired
ibmxnsErrTTLExpired.description: Number of Error packets generated because an IDP datagram was dropped because its time-to-live counter had expired.

ibmxnsErrTooBig.name: ibmxnsErrTooBig
ibmxnsErrTooBig.description: Number of Error packets generated because an IDP datagram was dropped because it was too large to be forwarded through this node.

ibmxnsErrResources.name: ibmxnsErrResources
ibmxnsErrResources.description: Number of Error packets generated because an IDP datagram was dropped due to lack of resources.

ibmxnsErrCongWarn.name: ibmxnsErrCongWarn
ibmxnsErrCongWarn.description: Number of Error packets generated for congestion warnings.

ibmxnsErrCongDiscard.name: ibmxnsErrCongDiscard
ibmxnsErrCongDiscard.description: Number of Error packets generated for congestion discards.

ibmxnsErrSquelched.name: ibmxnsErrSquelched
ibmxnsErrSquelched.description: Number of error packets that would have been generated, except that the faulted datagram had one of the following conditions: - was sent as link layer broadcast - NS destination was broadcast - NS source was 0, loopback, or broadcast

ibmxnsErrOutMsgs.name: ibmxnsErrOutMsgs
ibmxnsErrOutMsgs.description: Total number of error packets generated.

ibmxnsAddrEntry.name: ibmxnsAddrEntry
ibmxnsAddrEntry.description: An entry in the XNS address table.

ibmxnsAddrAddress.name: ibmxnsAddrAddress
ibmxnsAddrAddress.description: The XNS address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

ibmxnsAddrIfIndex.name: ibmxnsAddrIfIndex
ibmxnsAddrIfIndex.description: The interface index which identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

ibmxnsRouteEntry.name: ibmxnsRouteEntry
ibmxnsRouteEntry.description: An entry in the XNS route table.

ibmxnsRouteDest.name: ibmxnsRouteDest
ibmxnsRouteDest.description: The desination network of this route.

ibmxnsRouteIfIndex.name: ibmxnsRouteIfIndex
ibmxnsRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

ibmxnsRouteNextHop.name: ibmxnsRouteNextHop
ibmxnsRouteNextHop.description: The XNS network address of the next hop of this route.

ibmxnsRouteMetric.name: ibmxnsRouteMetric
ibmxnsRouteMetric.description: The hop count to the destination.

ibmxnsFilterEntry.name: ibmxnsFilterEntry
ibmxnsFilterEntry.description: An entry in the XNS filter table.

ibmxnsFilterIfIndex.name: ibmxnsFilterIfIndex
ibmxnsFilterIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ibmxnsFilterNumber.name: ibmxnsFilterNumber
ibmxnsFilterNumber.description: A unique integer identifying this filter entry for this interface.

ibmxnsFilterValue.name: ibmxnsFilterValue
ibmxnsFilterValue.description: An octet string representing the IDP header information required by this filter entry. Incoming IDP packets will be bitwise ANDed with the value of ibmxnsFilterMask, and if the result is equal to the value of this object, the packet will be filtered according to the value of ibmxnsFilterType. The structure of an IDP header is as follows: BIT16 checksum BIT16 length BIT8 transport control (ie. hop count) BIT8 packet type BIT32 destination network address BIT48 destination host address BIT16 destination socket BIT32 source network address BIT48 source host address BIT16 source socket

ibmxnsFilterMask.name: ibmxnsFilterMask
ibmxnsFilterMask.description: An octet string indicating the parts of the IDP header relevant to this filter entry. This mask will be bitwise ANDed with the IDP packet; if the result is equal to the value of ibmxnsFilterValue, the packet will be filtered according to the value of ibmxnsFilterType.

ibmxnsFilterType.name: ibmxnsFilterType
ibmxnsFilterType.description: Determines whether this filter is a deny entry or a permit entry.

ibmxnsFilterHCCompare.name: ibmxnsFilterHCCompare
ibmxnsFilterHCCompare.description: Indicates the relational association desired if filtering is being done based on hop count. If filtering is not being done based on hop count (that is, if the hop count portion of ibmxnsFilterMask is 0) the value of this object will be none(1).

ibmxnsFilterUse.name: ibmxnsFilterUse
ibmxnsFilterUse.description: Usage count for this filter entry.

ibmipxidpForwarding.name: ibmipxidpForwarding
ibmipxidpForwarding.description: Indicates if this node is acting as an IPX router.

ibmipxConfigTable.name: ibmipxConfigTable
ibmipxConfigTable.description: The table of IPX configuration information gathered on a per-interface basis.

ibmipxConfigEntry.name: ibmipxConfigEntry
ibmipxConfigEntry.description: IPX configuration information for a single interface.

ibmipxPortIfIndex.name: ibmipxPortIfIndex
ibmipxPortIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ibmipxPortStatus.name: ibmipxPortStatus
ibmipxPortStatus.description: The status of the IPX protocol stack on this interface.

ibmipxidpChecksum.name: ibmipxidpChecksum
ibmipxidpChecksum.description: Indicates the type of checksumming being done by IDP.

ibmipxLoopbackActive.name: ibmipxLoopbackActive
ibmipxLoopbackActive.description: Indicates if this port will use the hardware to loopback locally addressed packets or return the packet to the system via a software loopback.

ibmipxidpInReceives.name: ibmipxidpInReceives
ibmipxidpInReceives.description: Total number of IDP datagrams received.

ibmipxidpBcastInReceives.name: ibmipxidpBcastInReceives
ibmipxidpBcastInReceives.description: Number of IDP broadcast datagrams received.

ibmipxidpInDiscards.name: ibmipxidpInDiscards
ibmipxidpInDiscards.description: Number of incoming IDP datagrams discarded due to lack of resources.

ibmipxidpInAddrErrors.name: ibmipxidpInAddrErrors
ibmipxidpInAddrErrors.description: Number of incoming IDP datagrams discarded because the network portion of the address did not match the configured address for this host.

ibmipxidpOutRequests.name: ibmipxidpOutRequests
ibmipxidpOutRequests.description: Number of IDP datagrams generated by local IDP user protocols. This counter does not include any datagrams counted in ibmipxidpForwDatagrams.

ibmipxidpBcastOutRequests.name: ibmipxidpBcastOutRequests
ibmipxidpBcastOutRequests.description: Number of IDP broadcast datagrams generated by local IDP user protocols. This counter does not include any datagrams counted in ibmipxidpForwDatagrams.

ibmipxidpForwDatagrams.name: ibmipxidpForwDatagrams
ibmipxidpForwDatagrams.description: Number of IDP datagrams for which an attempt was made to forward.

ibmipxidpOutDiscards.name: ibmipxidpOutDiscards
ibmipxidpOutDiscards.description: Total number of outgoing IDP datagrams discarded.

ibmipxidpOutNoRoutes.name: ibmipxidpOutNoRoutes
ibmipxidpOutNoRoutes.description: Number of outgoing IDP datagrams discarded because no route was available to the specified destination.

ibmipxidpRoutingDiscards.name: ibmipxidpRoutingDiscards
ibmipxidpRoutingDiscards.description: Number of routing entries discarded even though they were valid.

ibmipxidpZeroDirBcast.name: ibmipxidpZeroDirBcast
ibmipxidpZeroDirBcast.description: Number of IDP datagrams forwarded to the system due to zeronet broadcast.

ibmipxidpTooSmall.name: ibmipxidpTooSmall
ibmipxidpTooSmall.description: Number of IDP datagrams with len < the size of an IDP header.

ibmipxidpBadLen.name: ibmipxidpBadLen
ibmipxidpBadLen.description: Number of IDP datagrams with number of bytes in the packet less than the number of bytes specified in the IDP header field.

ibmipxidpBadSum.name: ibmipxidpBadSum
ibmipxidpBadSum.description: Number of IDP datagrams with a bad checksum

ibmipxidpBadTTL.name: ibmipxidpBadTTL
ibmipxidpBadTTL.description: Number of IDP datagrams with TTL value > IDP maximum hopcount of 16.

ibmipxAddrEntry.name: ibmipxAddrEntry
ibmipxAddrEntry.description: An entry in the IPX address table.

ibmipxAddrAddress.name: ibmipxAddrAddress
ibmipxAddrAddress.description: The IPX address to which this entry's addressing information pertains.

ibmipxAddrIfIndex.name: ibmipxAddrIfIndex
ibmipxAddrIfIndex.description: The interface index which identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

ibmipxRouteEntry.name: ibmipxRouteEntry
ibmipxRouteEntry.description: An entry in the IPX route table.

ibmipxRouteDest.name: ibmipxRouteDest
ibmipxRouteDest.description: The desination network of this route.

ibmipxRouteIfIndex.name: ibmipxRouteIfIndex
ibmipxRouteIfIndex.description: The index value which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached.

ibmipxRouteNextHop.name: ibmipxRouteNextHop
ibmipxRouteNextHop.description: The IPX network address of the next hop of this route.

ibmipxRouteMetric.name: ibmipxRouteMetric
ibmipxRouteMetric.description: The hop count to the destination.

ibmipxFilterEntry.name: ibmipxFilterEntry
ibmipxFilterEntry.description: An entry in the IPX filter table.

ibmipxFilterIfIndex.name: ibmipxFilterIfIndex
ibmipxFilterIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ibmipxFilterNumber.name: ibmipxFilterNumber
ibmipxFilterNumber.description: A unique integer identifying this filter entry for this interface.

ibmipxFilterValue.name: ibmipxFilterValue
ibmipxFilterValue.description: An octet string representing the IDP header information required by this filter entry. Incoming IDP packets will be bitwise ANDed with the value of ibmipxFilterMask, and if the result is equal to the value of this object, the packet will be filtered according to the value of ibmipxFilterType. The structure of an IDP header is as follows: BIT16 checksum BIT16 length BIT8 transport control (ie. hop count) BIT8 packet type BIT32 destination network address BIT48 destination host address BIT16 destination socket BIT32 source network address BIT48 source host address BIT16 source socket

ibmipxFilterMask.name: ibmipxFilterMask
ibmipxFilterMask.description: An octet string indicating the parts of the IDP header relevant to this filter entry. This mask will be bitwise ANDed with the IDP packet; if the result is equal to the value of ibmipxFilterValue, the packet will be filtered according to the value of ibmipxFilterType.

ibmipxFilterType.name: ibmipxFilterType
ibmipxFilterType.description: Determines whether this filter is a deny entry or a permit entry.

ibmipxFilterHCCompare.name: ibmipxFilterHCCompare
ibmipxFilterHCCompare.description: Indicates the relational association desired if filtering is being done based on hop count. If filtering is not being done based on hop count (that is, if the hop count portion of ibmipxFilterMask is 0) the value of this object will be none(1).

ibmipxFilterUse.name: ibmipxFilterUse
ibmipxFilterUse.description: Usage count for this filter entry.

ibmipxsapStatInRequests.name: ibmipxsapStatInRequests
ibmipxsapStatInRequests.description: Number of SAP requests received by this entity.

ibmipxsapStatOutRequests.name: ibmipxsapStatOutRequests
ibmipxsapStatOutRequests.description: Number of SAP requests sent by this entity.

ibmipxsapStatInResponses.name: ibmipxsapStatInResponses
ibmipxsapStatInResponses.description: Number of SAP responses received by this entity.

ibmipxsapStatOutResponses.name: ibmipxsapStatOutResponses
ibmipxsapStatOutResponses.description: Number of SAP responses sent by this entity.

ibmipxsapStatInErrors.name: ibmipxsapStatInErrors
ibmipxsapStatInErrors.description: Number of incoming SAP packets discarded due to errors.

ibmipxsapStatOutDiscards.name: ibmipxsapStatOutDiscards
ibmipxsapStatOutDiscards.description: Number of outgoing SAP packets discarded due to lack of resources.

ibmipxsapServerNet.name: ibmipxsapServerNet
ibmipxsapServerNet.description: The IPX network number of this server.

ibmipxsapServerHost.name: ibmipxsapServerHost
ibmipxsapServerHost.description: The IPX host address of this server.

ibmipxsapServerSocket.name: ibmipxsapServerSocket
ibmipxsapServerSocket.description: The IPX socket number this server uses to advertise its service.

ibmipxsapServerAge.name: ibmipxsapServerAge
ibmipxsapServerAge.description: The number of seconds since this server entry was updated by the SAP protocol.

ibmipxsapServerHops.name: ibmipxsapServerHops
ibmipxsapServerHops.description: The number of network hops required to reach this server.

ibmipxsapServerIfIndex.name: ibmipxsapServerIfIndex
ibmipxsapServerIfIndex.description: The interface which is used to reach this server. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object for the same interface.

ibmipxsapServerIndex.name: ibmipxsapServerIndex
ibmipxsapServerIndex.description: A unique number identifying servers advertised at the same IPX network and host address.

ibmipxsapServerRequestsFiltered.name: ibmipxsapServerRequestsFiltered
ibmipxsapServerRequestsFiltered.description: Number of times a request for this server has been filtered.

cylinkStatusTable.name: cylinkStatusTable
cylinkStatusTable.description: The cylink Status table. This table contains information about the current state of the Cylink CSUs attached to the system.

cylinkStatusEntry.name: cylinkStatusEntry
cylinkStatusEntry.description: An entry in the cylink Status table.

cylinkIndex.name: cylinkIndex
cylinkIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a cylink system interface. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value in an ifIndex object instance.

cylinkLinkState.name: cylinkLinkState
cylinkLinkState.description: The current state of the link. The meanings of the values are: cylinkNotConnected(1) The link is not physically connected to the CSU. This may be due to loss of input circuit or loss of output circuit. cylinkNoInput(2) The input circuit is not connected. cylinkNoOutput(3) The output circuit is not connected. cylinkConnected(4) The link is connected to the CSU.

cylinkLoopback.name: cylinkLoopback
cylinkLoopback.description: The loopback mode of the link. The meaning of values are: cylinkNoLoopback(1) The link is not in loopback mode. cylinkNearEndLoopback(2) The link has been placed in loopback mode at the near end: data is being looped back within the local CSU. cylinkFarEndLoopback(3) The link has been placed in loopback mode at the far end: data is being looped across the link to the remote CSU and back.

cylinkQRSS.name: cylinkQRSS
cylinkQRSS.description: The Quasi-Random Signal Sequence test mode of the CSU. The value of the meanings are: cylinkNoQRSS(1) The CSU is not in QRSS mode. cylinkQRSSMaster(2) The CSU is transmitting a QRSS test pattern. cylinkQRSSSlave(3) The CSU is receiving a QRSS test pattern.

cylinkConfigTable.name: cylinkConfigTable
cylinkConfigTable.description: The cylink Configuration table. This table contains information about the configuration of the Cylink CSUs attached to the system.

cylinkConfigEntry.name: cylinkConfigEntry
cylinkConfigEntry.description: An entry in the cylink Configuration table.

cylinkConfigIndex.name: cylinkConfigIndex
cylinkConfigIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the CSU to which this entry is applicable. The CSU identified by a particular value of this index is the same CSU as identified by the same value in a cylinkIndex object instance.

cylinkSerialNumber.name: cylinkSerialNumber
cylinkSerialNumber.description: The manufacturer's serial number of this CSU.

cylinkSoftwareVersion.name: cylinkSoftwareVersion
cylinkSoftwareVersion.description: The version number of the microcode running in the CSU.

cylinkDTEFraming.name: cylinkDTEFraming
cylinkDTEFraming.description: The DTE framing selected (D4, or ESF). Framing conversion is automatically performed at both ends if the DTE is D4 framed and the network interface is ESF framed.

cylinkNetworkFraming.name: cylinkNetworkFraming
cylinkNetworkFraming.description: The network framing selected (D4, or ESF). Framing conversion is automatically performed at both ends if the DTE is D4 framed and the network interface is ESF framed.

cylinkDTEDS1Mode.name: cylinkDTEDS1Mode
cylinkDTEDS1Mode.description: The DTE DS-1 mode selected (B8ZS, or AMI).

cylinkNetworkDS1Mode.name: cylinkNetworkDS1Mode
cylinkNetworkDS1Mode.description: The network DS-1 mode selected (B8ZS, or AMI).

cylinkOnesResponsibility.name: cylinkOnesResponsibility
cylinkOnesResponsibility.description: The component selected for Ones Density Responsibility (DTE, or CSU.

cylinkOnesControl.name: cylinkOnesControl
cylinkOnesControl.description: The Ones Density Control selected (LSB 24, D4 FRM, or ESF DL).

cylinkZeroProtection.name: cylinkZeroProtection
cylinkZeroProtection.description: The Consecutive Zero Control selected (15, or 80). This determines the the maximum number of consecutive zeros allowed in the data stream before a one is forced.

cylinkClockSource.name: cylinkClockSource
cylinkClockSource.description: The transmit clock source selected for NRZ DIUs (network, DTE, an external clock, or the CSU's internal clock).

cylinkClockFrequency.name: cylinkClockFrequency
cylinkClockFrequency.description: The external clock frequency selected (56 kHz, 256 kHz, 1.344 MHz, 1.544 MHz).

cylinkClockBackup.name: cylinkClockBackup
cylinkClockBackup.description: The transmit clock backup source selected for NRZ DIUs (network, DTE, an external clock, or the CSU's internal clock).

cylinkDIUFrequency.name: cylinkDIUFrequency
cylinkDIUFrequency.description: The DIU frequency selected for NRZ DIUs (767 kbps, 1.244 Mbps, 1.528 Mbps, 1.536 Mbps).

cylinkDIUTiming.name: cylinkDIUTiming
cylinkDIUTiming.description: The DIU transmit timing selected for NRZ DIUs (Send Timing, or Terminal Timing).

cylinkDialoutCapability.name: cylinkDialoutCapability
cylinkDialoutCapability.description: The DIU dial-out capability selected (polled, tone, or pulse).

cylinkDialoutHoldoff.name: cylinkDialoutHoldoff
cylinkDialoutHoldoff.description: The mininum time, in minutes, between successful CSU-to-NMS connections to report alarm conditions.

cylinkPrimaryPhone.name: cylinkPrimaryPhone
cylinkPrimaryPhone.description: The primary telephone number used by by the CSU to contact the NMS.

cylinkSecondaryPhone.name: cylinkSecondaryPhone
cylinkSecondaryPhone.description: The secondary telephone number used by by the CSU to contact the NMS.

cylinkAlarmRepeatTime.name: cylinkAlarmRepeatTime
cylinkAlarmRepeatTime.description: The interval, in minutes, that the CSU will insert duplicate messages in the alarm queue for persistant alarm conditions.

cylinkESThreshold.name: cylinkESThreshold
cylinkESThreshold.description: The threshold, in seconds, for the errored second value in the current 15-minute interval.

cylinkSecondaryContact.name: cylinkSecondaryContact
cylinkSecondaryContact.description: The state of the CSU secondary contact (open or closed).

ibmdot1dBaseBridgeAddress.name: ibmdot1dBaseBridgeAddress
ibmdot1dBaseBridgeAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. It is recommended that this be the numerically smallest MAC address of all ports that belong to this bridge. However it is only required to be unique. When concatenated with ibmdot1dStpPriority a unique BridgeIdentifier is formed which is used in the Spanning Tree Protocol.

ibmdot1dBaseNumPorts.name: ibmdot1dBaseNumPorts
ibmdot1dBaseNumPorts.description: The number of TB ports controlled by this bridging entity.

ibmdot1dBaseType.name: ibmdot1dBaseType
ibmdot1dBaseType.description: Indicates what type of bridging this bridge can perform. If a bridge is actually performing a certain type of bridging this will be indicated by entries in the port table for the given type.

ibmdot1dBasePortTable.name: ibmdot1dBasePortTable
ibmdot1dBasePortTable.description: A table that contains generic information about every port that is associated with this bridge.

ibmdot1dBasePortEntry.name: ibmdot1dBasePortEntry
ibmdot1dBasePortEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the bridge.

ibmdot1dBasePort.name: ibmdot1dBasePort
ibmdot1dBasePort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains bridge management information.

ibmdot1dBasePortIfIndex.name: ibmdot1dBasePortIfIndex
ibmdot1dBasePortIfIndex.description: The value of the instance of the ifIndex object, defined in RFC 1156, RFC 1213 for the interface corresponding to this port.

ibmdot1dBasePortCircuit.name: ibmdot1dBasePortCircuit
ibmdot1dBasePortCircuit.description: For a port which potentially has the same value of ibmdot1dBasePortIfIndex as another port on the same bridge, this object contains an identifier unique to this port. For example, in the case where multiple ports correspond one-to-one with multiple Frame Relay circuit's, this value provides the object identifier for the frame relay MIB. Fpr a port which has a unique value of ibmdot1dBasePortIfIndex, this object can have the value {0.0}.

ibmdot1dBasePortDelayExceededDiscards.name: ibmdot1dBasePortDelayExceededDiscards
ibmdot1dBasePortDelayExceededDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to excessive transit delay through the bridge.

ibmdot1dBasePortMtuExceededDiscards.name: ibmdot1dBasePortMtuExceededDiscards
ibmdot1dBasePortMtuExceededDiscards.description: The number of frames discarded by this port due to an excessive size.

ibmdot1dStpProtocolSpecification.name: ibmdot1dStpProtocolSpecification
ibmdot1dStpProtocolSpecification.description: An indication of what version of the Spanning Tree Protocol is being run. The value 'decLb100(2)' indicates the DEC LANbridge 100 Spanning Tree protocol. IEEE 802.1d implementations will return 'ieee8021d(3)'. If future versions of the IEEE Spanning Tree Protocol are released that are incompatible with the current version a new value will be defined.

ibmdot1dStpPriority.name: ibmdot1dStpPriority
ibmdot1dStpPriority.description: The value of the write-able portion of the Bridge ID, i.e., the first two octets of the (8 octet long) Bridge ID. The other (last) 6 octets of the Bridge ID are given by the value of ibmdot1dBaseBridgeAddress.

ibmdot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: ibmdot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange
ibmdot1dStpTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the last time a topology change was detected by the bridge entity.

ibmdot1dStpTopChanges.name: ibmdot1dStpTopChanges
ibmdot1dStpTopChanges.description: The total number of topology changes detected by this bridge since the management entity was last reset or initialized.

ibmdot1dStpDesignatedRoot.name: ibmdot1dStpDesignatedRoot
ibmdot1dStpDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the root of the spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

ibmdot1dStpRootCost.name: ibmdot1dStpRootCost
ibmdot1dStpRootCost.description: The cost of the path to the root as seen from this bridge.

ibmdot1dStpRootPort.name: ibmdot1dStpRootPort
ibmdot1dStpRootPort.description: The port number of the port which offers the lowest cost path from this bridge to the root bridge.

ibmdot1dStpMaxAge.name: ibmdot1dStpMaxAge
ibmdot1dStpMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

ibmdot1dStpHelloTime.name: ibmdot1dStpHelloTime
ibmdot1dStpHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on any port when it is the root of the spanning tree or trying to become so, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

ibmdot1dStpHoldTime.name: ibmdot1dStpHoldTime
ibmdot1dStpHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

ibmdot1dStpForwardDelay.name: ibmdot1dStpForwardDelay
ibmdot1dStpForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in a particular state before moving to the next state. For example, how long a port stays in the Listening state when moving from Blocking to Learning. This value is also used, when a topology change has been detected and is underway, to age all dynamic entries in the Forwarding Database. (Note that this value is the one that this bridge is currently using, in contrast to ibmdot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay which is the value that this bridge and all others would start using if/when this bridge were to become the root.)

ibmdot1dStpBridgeMaxAge.name: ibmdot1dStpBridgeMaxAge
ibmdot1dStpBridgeMaxAge.description: The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1d/D9 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of ibmdot1dStpBridgeHelloTime. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1d/D9 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.
