The IBM 6611 Network Processor obtains this value from the 'Max Age' parameter provided to the configuration program.

ibmdot1dStpBridgeHelloTime.name: ibmdot1dStpBridgeHelloTime
ibmdot1dStpBridgeHelloTime.description: The value that all bridges use for HelloTime when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1d/D9 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds. The IBM 6611 Network Processor obtains this value from the 'Hello Time' parameter provided to the configuration program.

ibmdot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay.name: ibmdot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay
ibmdot1dStpBridgeForwardDelay.description: The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1d/D9 specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of ibmdot1dStpBridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified by 802.1d/D9 to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds. The IBM 6611 Network Processor obtains this value from the 'Forward Delay Time' parameter provided to the configuration program.

ibmdot1dStpPortTable.name: ibmdot1dStpPortTable
ibmdot1dStpPortTable.description: A table that contains port-specific information for the Spanning Tree Protocol.

ibmdot1dStpPortEntry.name: ibmdot1dStpPortEntry
ibmdot1dStpPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port about the Spanning Tree Protocol state for that port.

ibmdot1dStpPort.name: ibmdot1dStpPort
ibmdot1dStpPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Spanning Tree Protocol management information. This port number is the same as that reported by ibmdot1dBasePort.

ibmdot1dStpPortPriority.name: ibmdot1dStpPortPriority
ibmdot1dStpPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) octet of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of ibmdot1dStpPort.

ibmdot1dStpPortState.name: ibmdot1dStpPortState
ibmdot1dStpPortState.description: The port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the broken(6) state. For ports which are disabled (see ibmdot1dStpPortEnable), this object will have a value of disabled(1).

ibmdot1dStpPortEnable.name: ibmdot1dStpPortEnable
ibmdot1dStpPortEnable.description: The enabled/disabled status of the port.

ibmdot1dStpPortPathCost.name: ibmdot1dStpPortPathCost
ibmdot1dStpPortPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. The IBM 6611 Network Processor obtains this value from the 'Path Cost' parameter provided to the configuration program.

ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedRoot.name: ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedRoot
ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the Bridge recorded as the Root in the Configuration BPDUs transmitted by the Designated Bridge for the segment to which the port is attached.

ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedCost.name: ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedCost
ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedBridge.name: ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedBridge
ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedPort.name: ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedPort
ibmdot1dStpPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

ibmdot1dStpPortForwardTransitions.name: ibmdot1dStpPortForwardTransitions
ibmdot1dStpPortForwardTransitions.description: The number of times this port has transitioned from the Learning state to the Forwarding state.

ibmdot1dTpLearnedEntryDiscards.name: ibmdot1dTpLearnedEntryDiscards
ibmdot1dTpLearnedEntryDiscards.description: The total number of Forwarding Database entries, which have been or would have been learnt, but have been discarded due to a lack of space to store them in the Forwarding Database. If this counter is increasing, it indicates that the Forwarding Database is regularly becoming full (a condition which has unpleasant performance effects on the subnetwork). If this counter has a significant value but is not presently increasing, it indicates that the problem has been occurring but is not persistent.

ibmdot1dTpAgingTime.name: ibmdot1dTpAgingTime
ibmdot1dTpAgingTime.description: The timeout period in seconds for aging out dynamically learned forwarding information. The IBM 6611 Network Processor obtains this value from the 'Aging Time' parameter provided to the configuration program.

ibmdot1dTpFdbTable.name: ibmdot1dTpFdbTable
ibmdot1dTpFdbTable.description: A table that contains information about unicast entries for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information. This information is used by the transparent bridging function in determining how to propagate a received frame.

ibmdot1dTpFdbEntry.name: ibmdot1dTpFdbEntry
ibmdot1dTpFdbEntry.description: Information about a specific unicast MAC address for which the bridge has some forwarding and/or filtering information.

ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress.name: ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress
ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress.description: A unicast MAC address for which the bridge has forwarding and/or filtering information.

ibmdot1dTpFdbPort.name: ibmdot1dTpFdbPort
ibmdot1dTpFdbPort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port on which a frame having a source address equal to the value of the corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress has been seen. A value of '0' indicates that the port number has not been learned but that the bridge does have some forwarding/filtering information about this address (e.g. in the ibmdot1dStaticTable). Implementors are encouraged to assign the port value to this object whenever it is learned even for addresses for which the corresponding value of ibmdot1dTpFdbStatus is not learned(3).

ibmdot1dTpFdbStatus.name: ibmdot1dTpFdbStatus
ibmdot1dTpFdbStatus.description: The status of this entry. The meanings of the values are: other(1) : none of the following. This would include the case where some other MIB object (not the corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbPort, nor an entry in the ibmdot1dStaticTable) is being used to determine if and how frames addressed to the value of the corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress are being forwarded. invalid(2) : this entry is not longer valid (e.g., it was learned but has since aged-out), but has not yet been flushed from the table. learned(3) : the value of the corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbPort was learned, and is being used. self(4) : the value of the corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress represents one of the bridge's addresses. The corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbPort indicates which of the bridge's ports has this address. mgmt(5) : the value of the corresponding instance of ibmdot1dTpFdbAddress is also the value of an existing instance of ibmdot1dStaticAddress.

ibmdot1dTpPortTable.name: ibmdot1dTpPortTable
ibmdot1dTpPortTable.description: A table that contains information about every port that is associated with this transparent bridge.

ibmdot1dTpPortEntry.name: ibmdot1dTpPortEntry
ibmdot1dTpPortEntry.description: A list of information for each port of a transparent bridge.

ibmdot1dTpPort.name: ibmdot1dTpPort
ibmdot1dTpPort.description: The port number of the port for which this entry contains Transparent bridging management information.

ibmdot1dTpPortMaxInfo.name: ibmdot1dTpPortMaxInfo
ibmdot1dTpPortMaxInfo.description: The maximum size of the INFO (non-MAC) field that this port will receive or transmit.

ibmdot1dTpPortInFrames.name: ibmdot1dTpPortInFrames
ibmdot1dTpPortInFrames.description: The number of frames that have been received by this port from its segment. Note that a frame received on the interface corresponding to this port is only counted by this object if and only if it is for a protocol being processed by the local bridging function.

ibmdot1dTpPortOutFrames.name: ibmdot1dTpPortOutFrames
ibmdot1dTpPortOutFrames.description: The number of frames that have been transmitted by this port to its segment. Note that a frame transmitted on the interface corresponding to this port is only counted by this object if and only if it is for a protocol being processed by the local bridging function.

ibmdot1dTpPortInDiscards.name: ibmdot1dTpPortInDiscards
ibmdot1dTpPortInDiscards.description: Count of valid frames received which were discarded (i.e., filtered) by the Forwarding Process.

ibmdot1dStaticTable.name: ibmdot1dStaticTable
ibmdot1dStaticTable.description: A table containing filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from specific ports and containing specific destination addresses are allowed to be forwarded. The value of zero in this table as the port number from which frames with a specific destination address are received, is used to specify all ports for which there is no specific entry in this table for that particular destination address. Entries are valid for unicast and for group/broadcast addresses.

ibmdot1dStaticEntry.name: ibmdot1dStaticEntry
ibmdot1dStaticEntry.description: Filtering information configured into the bridge by (local or network) management specifying the set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and containing a specific destination address are allowed to be forwarded.

ibmdot1dStaticAddress.name: ibmdot1dStaticAddress
ibmdot1dStaticAddress.description: The destination MAC address in a frame to which this entry's filtering information applies. This object can take the value of a unicast address, a group address or the broadcast address.

ibmdot1dStaticReceivePort.name: ibmdot1dStaticReceivePort
ibmdot1dStaticReceivePort.description: Either the value '0', or the port number of the port from which a frame must be received in order for this entry's filtering information to apply. A value of zero indicates that this entry applies on all ports of the bridge for which there is no other applicable entry.

ibmdot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo.name: ibmdot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo
ibmdot1dStaticAllowedToGoTo.description: The set of ports to which frames received from a specific port and destined for a specific MAC address, are allowed to be forwarded. Each octet within the value of this object specifies a set of eight ports, with the first octet specifying ports 1 through 8, the second octet specifying ports 9 through 16, etc. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the bridge is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'. (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant.)

ibmdot1dStaticStatus.name: ibmdot1dStaticStatus
ibmdot1dStaticStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other(1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid(2) - writing this value to the object removes the corresponding entry. permanent(3) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so after the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnReset(4) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until the next reset of the bridge. deleteOnTimeout(5) - this entry is currently in use and will remain so until it is aged out.

ibmdecNodeType.description: This parameter indicates the node type of the router. This object is the same as the phivRouteType object defined by RFC 1289, however, this definition extends the enumerations to provide new values.

ibmdecLANCircuitTable.name: ibmdecLANCircuitTable
ibmdecLANCircuitTable.description: The list of information relevant to LAN circuits. This table extends the information provided by the phivCircuitParametersTable defined by RFC 1289.

ibmdecLANCircuitEntry.name: ibmdecLANCircuitEntry
ibmdecLANCircuitEntry.description: Table entry with information relevant to LAN circuits.

ibmdecLANCircuitIndex.name: ibmdecLANCircuitIndex
ibmdecLANCircuitIndex.description: A unique index value for each known circuit on a LAN interface. The value of this variable is the same as that provided by phivCircuitIndex.

ibmdecLANCircuitType.name: ibmdecLANCircuitType
ibmdecLANCircuitType.description: If the CircuitType is Bilingual for a circuit, the router would use a Phase_IV compliant locally administered MAC address for that circuit and would be configured to communicate with Phase_IV and Phase_IV-Prime nodes over that circuit. A bilingual router can help communication between the Phase_IV and the Phase_IV-Prime nodes over the same extended LAN segment, and prevents a partitioned network. If the CircuitType is AMA ( Arbitrary MAC Address ) for a circuit, the router would use an arbitrary MAC address for that circuit, and would be configured to communicate with Phase_IV-Prime nodes over that circuit. If the CircuitType is PhaseIV for a circuit, the router would use the Phase_IV compliant locally administered MAC address for that circuit, and would be configured to communicate with Phase_IV nodes over that circuit.

ibmdecLANCircuitSourceRoute.name: ibmdecLANCircuitSourceRoute
ibmdecLANCircuitSourceRoute.description: This parameter indicates if source routing is enabled on a token-ring circuit. A value of 3 is returned for circuits which are not of the 802.5/token-ring type.

ibmdecLANCircuitAddrType.name: ibmdecLANCircuitAddrType
ibmdecLANCircuitAddrType.description: This parameter indicates the type of MAC address used on this circuit. The value returned is decnet(1), if a DECnet Phase_IV compliant locally administered MAC address is being used. The value returned is hardware(2), if the unique assigned ROM address is used. The value returned is user(3), if a non DECnet Phase_IV compliant locally administered MAC address is being used.

ibmipPtyQueueEnableTable.name: ibmipPtyQueueEnableTable
ibmipPtyQueueEnableTable.description: This table defines which interfaces are enabled for IP prioritization. It also defines the default serial transmission priority queue to be used for IP packets which are not assigned to use a specific transmission queue.

ibmipPtyQueueEnable.name: ibmipPtyQueueEnable
ibmipPtyQueueEnable.description: The value of this object identifies if IP prioritization is enabled on this interface.

ibmipPtyQueueDefault.name: ibmipPtyQueueDefault
ibmipPtyQueueDefault.description: Identifies the transmission queue to be used for IP packets which are not assigned to use a specific transmission queue.

ibmipPtyQueueTable.name: ibmipPtyQueueTable
ibmipPtyQueueTable.description: This table contains the assignments of UDP/TCP port numbers to specific transmission queues for a given serial interface.

ibmipPtyQueueEntry.name: ibmipPtyQueueEntry
ibmipPtyQueueEntry.description: Each entry defines the UDP/TCP port number and its associated transmission priority queue for a given interface.

ibmipPtyQueueIfIndex.name: ibmipPtyQueueIfIndex
ibmipPtyQueueIfIndex.description: Defines the interface on which a UDP/TCP port is associated with a specific transmission priority queue. This interface is the same interface as defined by the ifIndex variable of the MIB-II interfaces group.

ibmipPtyQueuePort.name: ibmipPtyQueuePort
ibmipPtyQueuePort.description: Identifies a UDP or TCP port number.

ibmipPtyQueueType.name: ibmipPtyQueueType
ibmipPtyQueueType.description: Indicates the port type of the port number defined by ibmipPtyQueuePort.

ibmipPtyQueueNumber.name: ibmipPtyQueueNumber
ibmipPtyQueueNumber.description: Indicates which transmission queue will be used to transmit a packet which has a port number as specified by ibmipPtyQueuePort.

ibmipFilterTable.name: ibmipFilterTable
ibmipFilterTable.description: Table of IP address/mask filter definitions.

ibmipFilterEntry.name: ibmipFilterEntry
ibmipFilterEntry.description: An entry in the IP address/mask filter table.

ibmipFilterIfIndex.name: ibmipFilterIfIndex
ibmipFilterIfIndex.description: Defines the interface associated with this address/mask filter definition. This interface is the same interface as defined by the ifIndex variable of the MIB-II interfaces group.

ibmipFilterId.name: ibmipFilterId
ibmipFilterId.description: An id that defines this filter entry. This number is unique within this interface.

ibmipFilterScope.name: ibmipFilterScope
ibmipFilterScope.description: Defines whether this filter is applied to all interfaces or just this one.

ibmipPermitDeny.name: ibmipPermitDeny
ibmipPermitDeny.description: Identifies whether traffic for a specified filter ID is to be permitted to pass through the IBM 6611 or whether it is to be discarded.

ibmipFilterAddr1.name: ibmipFilterAddr1
ibmipFilterAddr1.description: A valid IP address of the host, subnet or network for this filter. For singular filters, this is the only end point, however, for dual filters this is the source end point.

ibmipFilterMask1.name: ibmipFilterMask1
ibmipFilterMask1.description: A valid IP address mask used for this filter. In conjunction with the IP address defined by ibmipFilterAddr1, it defines the range of IP addresses to be filtered.

ibmipFilterAddr2.name: ibmipFilterAddr2
ibmipFilterAddr2.description: Defines the destination IP address if ibmipFilterType is dual. This value is undefined for singular filters.

ibmipFilterMask2.name: ibmipFilterMask2
ibmipFilterMask2.description: A valid IP address mask used for this filter. In conjunction with the IP address defined by ibmipFilterAddr2, it defines the range of IP addresses to be filtered.

ibmipFilterExtTable.name: ibmipFilterExtTable
ibmipFilterExtTable.description: Table of IP port number filter definitions.

ibmipFilterExtEntry.name: ibmipFilterExtEntry
ibmipFilterExtEntry.description: An entry in the IP port number filter table.

ibmipFilterExtIfIndex.name: ibmipFilterExtIfIndex
ibmipFilterExtIfIndex.description: Defines the interface associated with this IP port number filter definition. This interface is the same interface as defined by the ifIndex variable of the MIB-II interfaces group.

ibmipFilterExtFilterId.name: ibmipFilterExtFilterId
ibmipFilterExtFilterId.description: An id that defines this filter entry. This number is unique within this interface and is the same filter ID as defined by ibmipFilterId.

ibmipFilterExtValue.name: ibmipFilterExtValue
ibmipFilterExtValue.description: Defines a TCP or UDP port number that will be filtered using this filter specification.

ibmipFilterExtProtocol.name: ibmipFilterExtProtocol
ibmipFilterExtProtocol.description: Specifies the protocol associated with the value defined by ibmipFilterExtValue for this filter specification.

ibmPtyQueueingTable.name: ibmPtyQueueingTable
ibmPtyQueueingTable.description: This table provides information on a specific transmission queue of a serial interface. Information includes: - Link Bandwidth Allocation (LBA): Identifies the number of packets transmitted from a particular queue before a lower priority transmission queue will be serviced. - Queue Bandwidth Reservation (QBR): Identifies the percentage of buffer space on a serial adapter that is allotted to a particular queue for transmission of packets.

ibmPtyQueueingEntry.name: ibmPtyQueueingEntry
ibmPtyQueueingEntry.description: Each entry defines the Link Bandwidth Allocation (LBA) and Queue Bandwidth Reservation (QBR) definitions for a specific transmission queue on a serial interface. Additionally, a counter is provided indicating the number of packets discarded on this queue due to a queue overflow.

ibmPtyQueueingIfIndex.name: ibmPtyQueueingIfIndex
ibmPtyQueueingIfIndex.description: Defines the interface associated with this priority queue information. This interface is the same interface as defined by the ifIndex variable of the MIB-II interfaces group.

ibmPtyQueueingQnum.name: ibmPtyQueueingQnum
ibmPtyQueueingQnum.description: Identifies the priority queue associated with this interface and its priority queue information.

ibmPtyQueueingLBA.name: ibmPtyQueueingLBA
ibmPtyQueueingLBA.description: Link Bandwidth Allocation (LBA): Identifies the number of packets that will be transmitted from this queue before a lower priority queue will be serviced.

ibmPtyQueueingQBR.name: ibmPtyQueueingQBR
ibmPtyQueueingQBR.description: Queue Bandwidth Reservation (QBR): Identifies the percentage of buffer space on a serial adapter that is allotted to a particular queue for transmission of packets. The sum of all QBR values on an interface must add up to 100%.

ibmPtyQueueingDiscards.name: ibmPtyQueueingDiscards
ibmPtyQueueingDiscards.description: Identifies the number of packets discarded from this queue due to a queue overflow.

ibmTGTable.name: ibmTGTable
ibmTGTable.description: This table provides information about serial point-to-point links which are participating in the 2 T1 in a transmission group (TG) function.

ibmTGEntry.name: ibmTGEntry
ibmTGEntry.description: Each entry identifies an interface participating in the 2 T1 in a TG function, along with its associated TG name and which protocol is using the function.

ibmTGProtocol.name: ibmTGProtocol
ibmTGProtocol.description: Defines the protocol that is supported for this particular interface and TG name. Currently, only the IP protocol is supported

ibmTGIfIndex.name: ibmTGIfIndex
ibmTGIfIndex.description: Defines the interface associated with this particular TG name and protocol. This interface is the same interface as defined by the ifIndex variable of the MIB-II interfaces group.

ibmTGEnable.name: ibmTGEnable
ibmTGEnable.description: Defines whether the 2 T1 in a TG function is enabled on this interface

ibmTGGroupName.name: ibmTGGroupName
ibmTGGroupName.description: Defines the common TG name assigned to all interfaces in this group. All interfaces with the same TG name will belong to the same group.

ibmTGSwitchOuts.name: ibmTGSwitchOuts
ibmTGSwitchOuts.description: Counts the number of times a packet had to be switched to another interface in the transmission group.

ibmvSysRtr.name: ibmvSysRtr
ibmvSysRtr.description: Indicates whether this node is acting as a VINES router.

ibmvRouterName.name: ibmvRouterName
ibmvRouterName.description: The name of the router node, up to 15 characters long.

ibmvRouterNetid.name: ibmvRouterNetid
ibmvRouterNetid.description: The VINES network ID of the router node equal to the router node's serial number. This id may be up to 4 bytes in length.

ibmvipTotalIn.name: ibmvipTotalIn
ibmvipTotalIn.description: The total number of VINES IP packets that the router node has received since the last reboot.

ibmvipTotalOut.name: ibmvipTotalOut
ibmvipTotalOut.description: The total number of VINES IP packets that the router node has sent since the last reboot.

ibmvipRouted.name: ibmvipRouted
ibmvipRouted.description: The total number of packets that were routed to another node since the last reboot.

ibmvipBcast.name: ibmvipBcast
ibmvipBcast.description: The number of VINES IP broadcast packets sent, both generated from the router node and routed from other nodes, since the last reboot.

ibmvipInReceives.name: ibmvipInReceives
ibmvipInReceives.description: The number of unicast VINES IP packets received since the last reboot. A unicast packet is destined for this particular router node. It is not being forwarded, multicasted or broadcasted.

ibmvipBcastInReceives.name: ibmvipBcastInReceives
ibmvipBcastInReceives.description: The number of VINES IP broadcast packets received since the last reboot.

ibmvipBad.name: ibmvipBad
ibmvipBad.description: The total number of badly formed packets that the router node has received since the last booted.

ibmvipBadHeaders.name: ibmvipBadHeaders
ibmvipBadHeaders.description: The number of incoming VINES IP packets received since the last reboot which contained a header error; excluding the following errors: length, checksum and time to live.

ibmvipTooSmalls.name: ibmvipTooSmalls
ibmvipTooSmalls.description: The number of VINES IP packets received since the last reboot with len < the size of a VINES IP header.

ibmvipBadLens.name: ibmvipBadLens
ibmvipBadLens.description: The number of VINES IP packets received since the last reboot whose packet size is not equal to the number of bytes specified in the VINES IP header field.

ibmvipBadSums.name: ibmvipBadSums
ibmvipBadSums.description: The number of VINES IP packets received since the last reboot with a bad checksum.

ibmvipInDiscards.name: ibmvipInDiscards
ibmvipInDiscards.description: The number of incoming VINES IP packets discarded since the last reboot due to lack of resources.

ibmvipZeroHops.name: ibmvipZeroHops
ibmvipZeroHops.description: The number of VINES IP packets discarded since the last reboot because the hop count equals zero and the current node is not the destination.

ibmvipOutNoRoutes.name: ibmvipOutNoRoutes
ibmvipOutNoRoutes.description: The number of outgoing VINES IP packets discarded since the last reboot because no route is available.

ibmvarpQueryReqs.name: ibmvarpQueryReqs
ibmvarpQueryReqs.description: The number of query requests received from clients since the last reboot. When a client is first booted up, it sends out a broadcast query request packet on its LAN segment.

ibmvarpServiceResps.name: ibmvarpServiceResps
ibmvarpServiceResps.description: The number of ARP query responses sent out from this router node since the last reboot. Each router node on the same LAN segment that is providing address assignments will respond.

ibmvarpAssignReqs.name: ibmvarpAssignReqs
ibmvarpAssignReqs.description: The number of ARP assignment request received from clients since the last reboot. The client issues an assignment request packet to the router node that responded first to the query request.

ibmvarpAssignResps.name: ibmvarpAssignResps
ibmvarpAssignResps.description: The number of ARP assignment responses sent to clients since the last reboot. The router node issues a VINES internet address for the client and sends it back in an assignment response packet.

ibmvarpHeaderError.name: ibmvarpHeaderError
ibmvarpHeaderError.description: The number of ARP packets received since the last reboot with a header error.

ibmvNbrNumber.name: ibmvNbrNumber
ibmvNbrNumber.description: The number of entries in the neighbor table.

ibmvNbrTable.name: ibmvNbrTable
ibmvNbrTable.description: A list of information about IBM's VINES router neighbor table.

ibmvNbrEntry.name: ibmvNbrEntry
ibmvNbrEntry.description: The information for each entry in the neighbor table.

ibmvNbrNetid.name: ibmvNbrNetid
ibmvNbrNetid.description: The network ID of the neighbor. The VINES internet address has the following form: 'nnnnnnnn.ssss'hex, where n = network ID and s = subnetwork ID. If the neighbor is a router, then network ID is the router node's (the neighbor's) serial number.

ibmvNbrSubNetid.name: ibmvNbrSubNetid
ibmvNbrSubNetid.description: The subnetwork ID of the neighbor. The VINES internet address has the following form: 'nnnnnnnn.ssss'hex, where n = network ID and s = subnetwork ID. If the neighbor is a router node, then the subnetwork ID for the router node (the neighbor) is 1.

ibmvNbrType.name: ibmvNbrType
ibmvNbrType.description: The type of the neighbor (workstation = pc).

ibmvNbrIfType.name: ibmvNbrIfType
ibmvNbrIfType.description: The type of interface that the server uses to reach the neighbor.

ibmvNbrRemAddress.name: ibmvNbrRemAddress
ibmvNbrRemAddress.description: The address of the neighbor's physical interface. For LAN's, it is the hardware address of the neighbor.

ibmvNbrLocAddress.name: ibmvNbrLocAddress
ibmvNbrLocAddress.description: The address of the router node's physical interface, such as a LAN address.

ibmvNbrLocSlot.name: ibmvNbrLocSlot
ibmvNbrLocSlot.description: The slot number of the interface card that the router node uses to reach the neighbor.

ibmvNbrLocPort.name: ibmvNbrLocPort
ibmvNbrLocPort.description: The port number on the interface card that the router node used to reach the neighbor.

ibmvNbrAging.name: ibmvNbrAging
ibmvNbrAging.description: The amount of time left before a neighbor entry will be removed because of aging. For a WAN link, which is defined to be permanent, this object is not applicable.

ibmvNbrFlags.name: ibmvNbrFlags
ibmvNbrFlags.description: Only applicable to a WAN link; states if the link is permanent or non-permanent.

ibmvNbrRIF.name: ibmvNbrRIF
ibmvNbrRIF.description: LAN - MAC address and if applicable, source routing information. Frame Relay - n/a PPP - n/a

ibmvNbrIfIndex.name: ibmvNbrIfIndex
ibmvNbrIfIndex.description: The interface (using the MIB II standard) used to reach the neighbor. This number corresponds to the IfIndex object found in MIB II.

ibmvNbrMetric.name: ibmvNbrMetric
ibmvNbrMetric.description: The cost to reach the neighbor.

ibmvRtCfgMax.name: ibmvRtCfgMax
ibmvRtCfgMax.description: The maximum number of entries allowed in the routing table. This value is not defined by administrator.

ibmvRtCfgInFlt.name: ibmvRtCfgInFlt
ibmvRtCfgInFlt.description: Enables or disables all inbound RTP filters defined. If no inbound RTP filters are defined, then this object has no effect. If a filter is defined, then the default value is 'enabled'.

ibmvRtCfgInFltNum.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltNum
ibmvRtCfgInFltNum.description: The number of inbound RTP filters currently defined.

ibmvRtCfgInFltTable.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltTable
ibmvRtCfgInFltTable.description: A list of information about the inbound RTP filters which are specified for this router node.

ibmvRtCfgInFltEntry.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltEntry
ibmvRtCfgInFltEntry.description: The information for each entry in the inbound RTP filter table.

ibmvRtCfgInFltNetID.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltNetID
ibmvRtCfgInFltNetID.description: Administrator defined object which specifies the VINES network number to be filtered on the port. The range of the network number is 00000000 - FFFFFFFE. If the network number, 0xFFFFFFFF, is defined, then all network numbers will be filtered.

ibmvRtCfgInFltIfIndex.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltIfIndex
ibmvRtCfgInFltIfIndex.description: The interface (using the MIB II standard) for which the inbound RTP filters were defined. This number corresponds to the IfIndex object found in MIB II.

ibmvRtCfgInFltMode.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltMode
ibmvRtCfgInFltMode.description: The filtering action for the inbound RTP filter. The inbound RTP filters operate on network numbers contained in the topological entries in the RTP update, response, and redirect packets received over a specified interface. In deny mode, the 6611 ignores route information for a network if the network number and the port on which the route information was received matches any inbound RTP filter. In permit mode, the IBM 6611 processes route information for a network only if the network number and the port on which the route information was received matches any inbound RTP filter. The default for this object is 'deny'.

ibmvRtCfgInFltUses.name: ibmvRtCfgInFltUses
ibmvRtCfgInFltUses.description: The number of times the defined filter was used.

ibmvRtCfgOutFlt.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFlt
ibmvRtCfgOutFlt.description: Enables or disables all outbound RTP filters defined. If no outbound RTP filters are defined, then this object has no effect. If a filter is defined, then the default value is 'enabled'.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltNum.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltNum
ibmvRtCfgOutFltNum.description: The number of outbound RTP filters currently defined.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltTable.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltTable
ibmvRtCfgOutFltTable.description: A list of information about the outbound RTP filters which are specified for this router node.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltEntry.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltEntry
ibmvRtCfgOutFltEntry.description: The information for each entry in the outbound RTP filter table.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltNetID.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltNetID
ibmvRtCfgOutFltNetID.description: Administrator defined object which specifies the VINES network number to be filtered on the port. The range of the network number is 00000000 - FFFFFFFE. If the network number, 0xFFFFFFFF, is defined, then all network numbers will be filtered.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltIfIndex.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltIfIndex
ibmvRtCfgOutFltIfIndex.description: The interface (using the MIB II standard) for which the outbound RTP filters were defined. This number corresponds to the IfIndex object found in MIB II.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltMode.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltMode
ibmvRtCfgOutFltMode.description: The filtering action for the outbound RTP filter. The outbound RTP filters operate on the network numbers contained in the topological entries in RTP update and response packets transmitted over a specified interface. In deny mode, filters operate on interface names and network numbers (that is, the network numbers contained in the topological entries in the RTP packets). In deny mode, the IBM 6611 does not advertise route information for a network if the network number and the interface on which the route information is to be transmitted matches any outbound RTP filter. In permit mode, the 6611 advertises route information for a network only if the network number and the interface on which the route information is to be transmitted matches any outbound RTP filter. The default for this object is 'Deny'.

ibmvRtCfgOutFltUses.name: ibmvRtCfgOutFltUses
ibmvRtCfgOutFltUses.description: The number of times the defined filter was used.

ibmvRtCfgFlt.name: ibmvRtCfgFlt
ibmvRtCfgFlt.description: Enables or disables all RTP router filters defined. If no RTP router filters are defined, then this object has no effect. If a filter is defined, then the default value is 'enabled'.

ibmvRtCfgFltNum.name: ibmvRtCfgFltNum
ibmvRtCfgFltNum.description: The number of RTP router filters currently defined.

ibmvRtCfgFltTable.name: ibmvRtCfgFltTable
ibmvRtCfgFltTable.description: A list of information about the RTP router filters which are specified for this router node.

ibmvRtCfgFltEntry.name: ibmvRtCfgFltEntry
ibmvRtCfgFltEntry.description: The information for each entry in the RTP router filter table.

ibmvRtCfgFltNetID.name: ibmvRtCfgFltNetID
ibmvRtCfgFltNetID.description: Administrator defined object which specifies the VINES network number to be filtered on the port. The range of the network number is 00000000 - FFFFFFFE. If the network number, 0xFFFFFFFF, is defined, then all network numbers will be filtered.

ibmvRtCfgFltMode.name: ibmvRtCfgFltMode
ibmvRtCfgFltMode.description: The filtering action for the RTP router filter. The RTP router filters operate on the network number contained in the source network number field in the IP header of any RTP packet (update, request, response, and redirect). (The subnetwork ID is assumed to be 0x0001.) In deny mode, the IBM 6611 ignores route information from a service node if the sending router's network number matches any RTP router filter. In permit mode, the IBM 6611 processes route information from a router only if the sending router's network number matches any RTP router filter. The default for this object is 'deny'.

ibmvRtCfgFltUses.name: ibmvRtCfgFltUses
ibmvRtCfgFltUses.description: The number of times the defined filter was used.

ibmvrtpUpdSents.name: ibmvrtpUpdSents
ibmvrtpUpdSents.description: The number of routing update packets sent since the last reboot. The routing update packets are periodically broadcast by nodes to notify neighboring nodes of their existence. Router nodes include network topology information in these updates.

ibmvrtpUpdRecs.name: ibmvrtpUpdRecs
ibmvrtpUpdRecs.description: The number of routing update packets received since the last reboot. The routing update packets are sent from neighboring node making known their existence. Packets received from router nodes include network topology information.

ibmvrtpReqSents.name: ibmvrtpReqSents
ibmvrtpReqSents.description: The number of routing request packets sent since the last reboot. Routing request packets are sent by a node when it requires an immediate update.

ibmvrtpReqRecs.name: ibmvrtpReqRecs
ibmvrtpReqRecs.description: The number of routing request packets received since the last reboot. The 6611 receives routing request packets when another node requires an immediate update. The 6611 will send the update in a routing response packet.

ibmvrtpResSents.name: ibmvrtpResSents
ibmvrtpResSents.description: The number of routing response packets sent since the last reboot. Routing response packets are sent in response to a routing request packet.

ibmvrtpResRecs.name: ibmvrtpResRecs
ibmvrtpResRecs.description: The number of routing response packets received since the last reboot. When a node sends out a routing request packet, it receives a routing response packet which contains all the routing information requested.

ibmvrtpRedSents.name: ibmvrtpRedSents
ibmvrtpRedSents.description: The number of routing redirect packets sent since the last reboot. The routing redirect packets are sent by a node to notify another node of a more direct path to a destination node.

ibmvrtpRedRecs.name: ibmvrtpRedRecs
ibmvrtpRedRecs.description: The number of routing redirect packets received since the last reboot. A 6611 receives a routing redirect packet when another node knows a more direct path to the destination node.

ibmvrtpHeaderError.name: ibmvrtpHeaderError
ibmvrtpHeaderError.description: The number of RTP packets received since the last reboot with a RTP header error.

ibmvRtNumber.name: ibmvRtNumber
ibmvRtNumber.description: The number of entires in the route table.

ibmvRtTable.name: ibmvRtTable
ibmvRtTable.description: A list of information about IBM's VINES router table.

ibmvRtEntry.name: ibmvRtEntry
ibmvRtEntry.description: The information for each entry in the router table.

ibmvRtNetid.name: ibmvRtNetid
ibmvRtNetid.description: The network ID of the router node's destination router node.

ibmvRtMetric.name: ibmvRtMetric
ibmvRtMetric.description: The routing metric used by the called router node to reach the destination. A routing metric is an estimated round-trip delay time associated with the router that maximum sized VINES IP packets will take to reach the destination. The metric reflects the cost of the path to the destination, it is in 200-millisecond units.

ibmvRtIdle.name: ibmvRtIdle
ibmvRtIdle.description: The time to live timer for this router node's entry. This value indicates the amount of time before the entry is removed from the called router node's routing table. The value is returned in 90 second units.

ibmvRtGateNetid.name: ibmvRtGateNetid
ibmvRtGateNetid.description: The network ID of the router node that acts as the router for reaching the destination router node.

ibmvRtIfIndex.name: ibmvRtIfIndex
ibmvRtIfIndex.description: The interface (using the MIB II standard) which identifies the local interface through which the next hop of this route should be reached. This number corresponds to the IfIndex object found in MIB II.

ibmvRtState.name: ibmvRtState
ibmvRtState.description: The state the routing entry; permanent or not permanent.

ibmvicpExcGens.name: ibmvicpExcGens
ibmvicpExcGens.description: Number of exception notifications generated from this router node since the last reboot.

ibmvicpMetricGens.name: ibmvicpMetricGens
ibmvicpMetricGens.description: The number of metric notifications generated from this router node since the last reboot. The ICP packet contains metric information about the final transmission medium used to reach a client node.

ibmvicpHeaderError.name: ibmvicpHeaderError
ibmvicpHeaderError.description: The number of ICP packets received since the last reboot with an ICP header error.

ibmvFRPreassembles.name: ibmvFRPreassembles
ibmvFRPreassembles.description: The number of times packets were reassembled since the last reboot. One VINES IP packet being broken into three message fragments is counted as one fragmentation. The three fragments being reassembled into one VINES IP packet counts as one reassembly.

ibmvFRPfragsReassembled.name: ibmvFRPfragsReassembled
ibmvFRPfragsReassembled.description: The number of fragments that were reassembled since the last reboot. If three fragments are to be reassembled into one packet, then this object value will add three to its total.

ibmvFRPreasFails.name: ibmvFRPreasFails
ibmvFRPreasFails.description: The number of times the reassembly of fragments fails since the last reboot.

ibmvFRPfragmented.name: ibmvFRPfragmented
ibmvFRPfragmented.description: The number of packet fragmentations performed since the last reboot.

ibmvFRPfrgCreated.name: ibmvFRPfrgCreated
ibmvFRPfrgCreated.description: The number of fragments created since the last reboot when fragmenting VINES IP packets. If a VINES IP packet is fragmented into three fragments, then this object value will add three to its total.

ibmvFRPfrgFails.name: ibmvFRPfrgFails
ibmvFRPfrgFails.description: The number of times the fragmentation of a VINES IP packets fails since the last reboot.

ibmvPortCfgTable.name: ibmvPortCfgTable
ibmvPortCfgTable.description: The list of information about port configuration at each interface.

ibmvPortCfgEntry.name: ibmvPortCfgEntry
ibmvPortCfgEntry.description: The information for each entry in the port configuration table.

ibmvPortCfgIfIndex.name: ibmvPortCfgIfIndex
ibmvPortCfgIfIndex.description: The interface (using the MIB II standard) which uniquely identifies each interface and allows multiple tables to be associated with a given interface. This number corresponds to the IfIndex object found in MIB II.

ibmvPortCfgARP.name: ibmvPortCfgARP
ibmvPortCfgARP.description: Administrator defined value which specifies whether the router node will assign VINES addresses to clients that reside on the LAN attached to this port. The default value for this object is 'disable'.

ibmvPortCfgServ.name: ibmvPortCfgServ
ibmvPortCfgServ.description: Administrator defined value specifying whether the serverless option is enables or disabled. When the serverless option is enabled; the router looks for particular broadcasts that clients use in finding the services on the VINES server. This allows client nodes on a serverless LAN to communicate with a VINES server more than one hop away. The default value for this object is 'disable'.

ibmvPortCfgHCtoServ.name: ibmvPortCfgHCtoServ
ibmvPortCfgHCtoServ.description: Administrator defined value which specifies the number of hops from the client to the router node.

ibmvPortCfgPerUpdate.name: ibmvPortCfgPerUpdate
ibmvPortCfgPerUpdate.description: Administrator defined value which specifies whether periodic updates will be sent over a WAN link.

ibmvPortCfgMetric.name: ibmvPortCfgMetric
ibmvPortCfgMetric.description: Administrator defined value for port metric. This value overrides the metric which is used by the IBM 6611 to make routing decisions. If no response is provided to this parameter, the IBM 6611 will use defaults contained within the MPNP program. These defaults are based on values assigned by Banyan Systems for its VINES servers. The port metric is a rough estimate of the round trip delay for a maximum sized VINES IP packet to travel to any neighbor on this port. The unit for the metric value is 200 milliseconds. The default metric for an Ethernet port is 2. The default metric for a Token-Ring is determined by the response to the Token-Ring Data Rate parameter. The default metric for a serial port is determined by the response to the Serial-Line Speed parameter.

ibmvPortCfgTR.name: ibmvPortCfgTR
ibmvPortCfgTR.description: Administrator defined value which determines the encapsulation method used for receiving and transmitting VINES packets on this port. IEEE 802.5 LLC uses 802.2 encapsulation followed by an LLC field using SAP value 0xBC You cannot use IEEE 802.5 LLC encapsulation on the same port that performs data link switching, if the 0xBC SAP has been configured for frame forwarding by the data link switching function. IEEE 802.5 SNAP uses 802.2 encapsulation followed by a SNAP header using the organizationally unique ID 0x08 00 4A, the protocol id 0x80C4 for VINES IP and the protocol id 0x80C5 for VINES Link Level Echo.

ibmvPortCfgEN.name: ibmvPortCfgEN
ibmvPortCfgEN.description: Administrator defined value which determines the encapsulation method used for receiving and transmitting VINES packets on this port. Ethernet II uses DIX encapsulation with a packet type 0x0BAD for VINES IP and 0x0BAF for VINES Link Level Echo. IEEE 802.3 SNAP uses 802.2 encapsulation followed by a SNAP header using the organizationally unique ID 0x08 00 4A, the protocol id 0x80C4 for VINES IP and the protocol id 0x80C5 for VINES Link Level Echo.

ibmvPortCfgInFlt.name: ibmvPortCfgInFlt
ibmvPortCfgInFlt.description: Administrator defined value which allows inbound port filters to be defined. The default value is 'disabled'.

ibmvPortCfgInFltNum.name: ibmvPortCfgInFltNum
ibmvPortCfgInFltNum.description: The number of inbound port filters defined for this port.

ibmvPortCfgOutFlt.name: ibmvPortCfgOutFlt
ibmvPortCfgOutFlt.description: Administrator defined value which allows outbound port filters to be defined. The default value is 'disabled'.

ibmvPortCfgOutFltNum.name: ibmvPortCfgOutFltNum
ibmvPortCfgOutFltNum.description: The number of outbound port filters defined for this port.

ibmvFltTable.name: ibmvFltTable
ibmvFltTable.description: The list of information about port filter configurations at each interface .

ibmvFltEntry.name: ibmvFltEntry
ibmvFltEntry.description: The information for each entry in the port filter configuration table.

ibmvFltIfIndex.name: ibmvFltIfIndex
ibmvFltIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains management information. The IfIndex allows a subset of the filter table to be associated with a particular interface.

ibmvFltNo.name: ibmvFltNo
ibmvFltNo.description: A unique integer identifying this filter entry for this interface.

ibmvFltMode.name: ibmvFltMode
ibmvFltMode.description: Identifies if the port filter is an inbound or outbound filter.

ibmvFltValue.name: ibmvFltValue
ibmvFltValue.description: An octet string representing the concatenation of VINES IP header fields and VINES transport header fields required by this filter entry. Incoming packets will be bitwise ANDed with the value of ibmvFltMask, and if the result is equal to the value of this object, the packet will be filtered according to the value of ibmvFltValue. Fields from VINES IP and transport headers used for filtering: field length field name ------------ ------------------------------ 8 BITS protocol type 4 BITS hop count 32 BITS destination network number 16 BITS destination subnetwork number 16 BITS destination port number 32 BITS source network number 16 BITS source subnetwork number 16 BITS source port number

ibmvFltMask.name: ibmvFltMask
ibmvFltMask.description: An octet string indicating the parts of the VIP header and transport header relevant to this filter entry. This mask will be bitwise ANDed with the appropriate header fields; if the result is equal to the value of ibmvnFilterValue, the packet will be filtered according to the value of ibmvnFilterType.

ibmvFltType.name: ibmvFltType
ibmvFltType.description: Administrator defined value which determines the filtering mode for all filters defined on this port. If the port is using Deny mode, then all packets matching a defined port filter will be discarded. If the port is using Permit mode, then only the packets matching a defined port filter will be forwarded. The default value is Deny.

ibmvFltHCCompare.name: ibmvFltHCCompare
ibmvFltHCCompare.description: Administrator defined value which indicates the relational association desired if filtering is being done based on hop count. If filtering is not being done based on hop count (that is, if the hop count portion of IBM VINES Port Mask is 0) the value of this object will be none(1).

ibmvFltUses.name: ibmvFltUses
ibmvFltUses.description: This object counts how many times the defined filter was used.

ibmvifNumber.name: ibmvifNumber
ibmvifNumber.description: The number of VINES interfaces configured on the router node.

ibmvifTable.name: ibmvifTable
ibmvifTable.description: List of interfaces with some statistics about each interface.

ibmvifSlot.name: ibmvifSlot
ibmvifSlot.description: The slot number of the interface's communications card.

ibmvifPort.name: ibmvifPort
ibmvifPort.description: The port number of the interface.

ibmvifDescr.name: ibmvifDescr
ibmvifDescr.description: A textual description of the interface.

ibmvifAddress.name: ibmvifAddress
ibmvifAddress.description: The physical address of the interface, applies to LAN interfaces only.

ibmvifInPkts.name: ibmvifInPkts
ibmvifInPkts.description: The total number of VINES IP packets that the router node received since the last reboot.

ibmvifInErrs.name: ibmvifInErrs
ibmvifInErrs.description: The total number of received VINES IP packets that contained errors since the last reboot.

ibmvifOutPkts.name: ibmvifOutPkts
ibmvifOutPkts.description: The total number of VINES IP packets that the router node sent since the last reboot.

ibmvifOutErrs.name: ibmvifOutErrs
ibmvifOutErrs.description: The total number of transmitted VINES IP packets that contained errors since the last reboot.

ibmappnNodeCpName.name: ibmappnNodeCpName
ibmappnNodeCpName.description: Administratively-assigned network name for this node in the format NETID.CPNAME.

ibmappnNodeNetid.name: ibmappnNodeNetid
ibmappnNodeNetid.description: Administratively-assigned APPN network identification, which can be from one to eight characters. This ID is used with the control point name to create a fully-qualified control point name.

ibmappnNodeBlockNum.name: ibmappnNodeBlockNum
ibmappnNodeBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexadecimal digits identify the product and are not configurable.

ibmappnNodeIdNum.name: ibmappnNodeIdNum
ibmappnNodeIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number form the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is include in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

ibmappnNodeType.name: ibmappnNodeType
ibmappnNodeType.description: Type of APPN node, either network, len, or end node.

ibmappnNodeUpTime.name: ibmappnNodeUpTime
ibmappnNodeUpTime.description: Time (in hundredths of a second) since this APPN node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeNegotLs.name: ibmappnNodeNegotLs
ibmappnNodeNegotLs.description: Indicates whether this node supports negotiable link stations.

ibmappnNodeSegReasm.name: ibmappnNodeSegReasm
ibmappnNodeSegReasm.description: Indicates whether this node supports segment reassembly. This is only supported when segment generation is also supported.

ibmappnNodeBindReasm.name: ibmappnNodeBindReasm
ibmappnNodeBindReasm.description: Indicates whether this node supports Bind segment reassembly. This will only be supported when Bind segment generation is also supported.

ibmappnNodeParallelTg.name: ibmappnNodeParallelTg
ibmappnNodeParallelTg.description: Indicates whether this node supports parallel TGs.

ibmappnNodeService.name: ibmappnNodeService
ibmappnNodeService.description: Indicates whether this node allows call-in from nodes not defined locally.

ibmappnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing.name: ibmappnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing
ibmappnNodeAdaptiveBindPacing.description: Indicates whether this node supports adaptive bind pacing.

ibmappnNodeNnRcvRegChar.name: ibmappnNodeNnRcvRegChar
ibmappnNodeNnRcvRegChar.description: Indicates whether this node supports receiving registered characteristics.

ibmappnNodeNnGateway.name: ibmappnNodeNnGateway
ibmappnNodeNnGateway.description: Indicates whether this is a gateway node.

ibmappnNodeNnCentralDirectory.name: ibmappnNodeNnCentralDirectory
ibmappnNodeNnCentralDirectory.description: Indicates whether this node supports central directory cache.

ibmappnNodeNnTreeCache.name: ibmappnNodeNnTreeCache
ibmappnNodeNnTreeCache.description: Indicates whether this node supports route tree cache.

ibmappnNodeNnTreeUpdate.name: ibmappnNodeNnTreeUpdate
ibmappnNodeNnTreeUpdate.description: Indicates whether this node supports incremental_tree_update, which is only supported when tree caching is supported.

ibmappnNodeNnRouteAddResist.name: ibmappnNodeNnRouteAddResist
ibmappnNodeNnRouteAddResist.description: Route addition resistance is a value that indicates the relative desirability of using this node for intermediate session traffic. The value, which can be any integer 0-255, is used in route computation. The lower the value, the more desirable the node is for intermediate routing.

ibmappnNodeNnIsr.name: ibmappnNodeNnIsr
ibmappnNodeNnIsr.description: Indicates whether the node supports intermediate session routing.

ibmappnNodeNnFrsn.name: ibmappnNodeNnFrsn
ibmappnNodeNnFrsn.description: Flow reduction sequence numbers (FRSNs) are associated with Topology Database Updates (TDUs) and are unique only within each APPN network node. A TDU can be associated with multiple APPN resources. This object is the last FRSN sent in a topology update to adjacent network nodes.

ibmappnNodeEnSegGen.name: ibmappnNodeEnSegGen
ibmappnNodeEnSegGen.description: Indicates whether this end node supports segment generation.

ibmappnNodeEnModeCosMap.name: ibmappnNodeEnModeCosMap
ibmappnNodeEnModeCosMap.description: Indicates whether this end node supports mode name to COS name mapping.

ibmappnNodeEnLocateCdinit.name: ibmappnNodeEnLocateCdinit
ibmappnNodeEnLocateCdinit.description: Indicates whether this end node supports Locate Cdinit.

ibmappnNodeEnSendRegNames.name: ibmappnNodeEnSendRegNames
ibmappnNodeEnSendRegNames.description: Indicates whether the node will register its LUs with the adjacent serving network node: NO - do not register names YES - register names

ibmappnNodeEnSendRegChar.name: ibmappnNodeEnSendRegChar
ibmappnNodeEnSendRegChar.description: Indicates whether this node supports send register characteristics, which is only supported when send registered names is also supported.

ibmappnNodePortTable.name: ibmappnNodePortTable
ibmappnNodePortTable.description: The Port table describes the configuration and current status of the ports used by APPN. The type of DLC is included in this table as a pointer to the DLC port specific tables.

ibmappnNodePortEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortEntry
ibmappnNodePortEntry.description: The Port Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortName.name: ibmappnNodePortName
ibmappnNodePortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortState.name: ibmappnNodePortState
ibmappnNodePortState.description: Indicates the current state of this port.

ibmappnNodePortDlcType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcType
ibmappnNodePortDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

ibmappnNodePortPortType.name: ibmappnNodePortPortType
ibmappnNodePortPortType.description: Identifies the type of line used by this port.

ibmappnNodePortSIMRIM.name: ibmappnNodePortSIMRIM
ibmappnNodePortSIMRIM.description: Indicates whether Set Initialization Mode (SIM) and Receive Initialization Mode (RIM) are supported.

ibmappnNodePortLsRole.name: ibmappnNodePortLsRole
ibmappnNodePortLsRole.description: Initial role for LSs activated through this port, where 'abm' indicates asynchronous balance mode.

ibmappnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize.name: ibmappnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize
ibmappnNodePortMaxRcvBtuSize.description: Maximum Basic Transmission Size (BTU) that a link station on this port can receive.

ibmappnNodePortMaxIframeWindow.name: ibmappnNodePortMaxIframeWindow
ibmappnNodePortMaxIframeWindow.description: Maximum number of I-frames that can be received by the XID sender before an acknowledgement is received.

ibmappnNodePortDefLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDefLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodePortDefLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortDefLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDefLsBadXids
ibmappnNodePortDefLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortDynLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDynLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodePortDynLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortDynLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodePortDynLsBadXids
ibmappnNodePortDynLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations on this port since the last time this port was started.

ibmappnNodePortSpecific.name: ibmappnNodePortSpecific
ibmappnNodePortSpecific.description: Identifies the port specific OBJECT IDENTIFIER that can provide additional information.

ibmappnNodePortIpEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortIpEntry
ibmappnNodePortIpEntry.description: The IP Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortIpName.name: ibmappnNodePortIpName
ibmappnNodePortIpName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortDlsEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortDlsEntry
ibmappnNodePortDlsEntry.description: The DLS Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortDlsName.name: ibmappnNodePortDlsName
ibmappnNodePortDlsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN DLS port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortTrEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortTrEntry
ibmappnNodePortTrEntry.description: The TR Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortTrName.name: ibmappnNodePortTrName
ibmappnNodePortTrName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this APPN port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceTable.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceTable
ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceTable.description: Port table generic DLC trace table.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceEntry.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceEntry
ibmappnNodePortDlcTraceEntry.description: The Port name and a dynamic integer are the index to this table.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracPortName.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracPortName
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracPortName.description: The Port name associated with this this trace table entry.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracIndex.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracIndex
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracIndex.description: This index value is updated every time a new trace entry is created which provides a means to retrieve only the updated entries and also provides a simple method of correlating the entries. The table will wrap when the table is full, which will result in previous entries being written over. The mangement station can over come this by retrieving the table using this index to retrieve only the new table entries.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracDlcType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracDlcType
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracLocalAddr.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracLocalAddr
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracLocalAddr.description: Local address in format described below: other = free form DisplayString ip = ld.ld.ld.ld/2d tr = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx dlsw = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx ethernet = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracRemoteAddr.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracRemoteAddr
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracRemoteAddr.description: Remote Address in the format described below: other = free form DisplayString ip = ld.ld.ld.ld/2d tr = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx dlsw = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx ethernet = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracMsgType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracMsgType
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracMsgType.description: Indicates the type of trace record entry

ibmappnNodePortDlcTracCmdType.name: ibmappnNodePortDlcTracCmdType
ibmappnNodePortDlcTracCmdType.description: Indicates the command type of the trace entry.

ibmappnNodeLsTable.name: ibmappnNodeLsTable
ibmappnNodeLsTable.description: This table contains detail information about the link station configuration and current status.

ibmappnNodeLsEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsEntry
ibmappnNodeLsEntry.description: This table is indexed by the link station name.

ibmappnNodeLsName.name: ibmappnNodeLsName
ibmappnNodeLsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsPortName.name: ibmappnNodeLsPortName
ibmappnNodeLsPortName.description: Administratively-assigned name for the port. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsDlcType.name: ibmappnNodeLsDlcType
ibmappnNodeLsDlcType.description: The type of DLC interface, distinguished according to the protocol immediately 'below' this layer.

ibmappnNodeLsDynamic.name: ibmappnNodeLsDynamic
ibmappnNodeLsDynamic.description: Identifies whether this resource is a dynamic link station. Dynamic link stations are created when adjacent nodes that have not been locally defined establish a connection with this node.

ibmappnNodeLsCpName.name: ibmappnNodeLsCpName
ibmappnNodeLsCpName.description: Fully-qualified name of the adjacent node for this link station. The name can be from three to seventeen characters. Format is netid.cpname.

ibmappnNodeLsTgNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsTgNum
ibmappnNodeLsTgNum.description: Number associated with the TG to this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsLimResource.name: ibmappnNodeLsLimResource
ibmappnNodeLsLimResource.description: Indicates whether the link station is a limited resource. If it is, the TG is deactivated when there are no sessions.

ibmappnNodeLsMigration.name: ibmappnNodeLsMigration
ibmappnNodeLsMigration.description: Indicates whether this link station will be used for connections to down-level or migration partners.

ibmappnNodeLsBlockNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsBlockNum
ibmappnNodeLsBlockNum.description: The block number is the first three digits of the node_id. These 3 hexideimal digits identify the product and are not configurable.

ibmappnNodeLsIdNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsIdNum
ibmappnNodeLsIdNum.description: The ID number is the last 5 digits of the node_id. These 5 hexadecimal digits are administratively defined and combined with the 3 digit block number form the node_id. This node_id is used to identify the local node and is include in APPN alerts as well as being included in XIDs. A unique value is required for connections to SNA sub-area.

ibmappnNodeLsCpCpSession.name: ibmappnNodeLsCpCpSession
ibmappnNodeLsCpCpSession.description: Indicates whether CP-CP sessions are supported by this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsTargetPacingCount.name: ibmappnNodeLsTargetPacingCount
ibmappnNodeLsTargetPacingCount.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired pacing window size for BINDs on this TG. The number is significant only when fixed bind pacing is being performed.

ibmappnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize.name: ibmappnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize
ibmappnNodeLsMaxSendBtuSize.description: Numeric value between 0 and 32767 inclusive indicating the desired number of bytes in a Basic Transmission Unit (BTU) that can be sent on this TG. This is an administratively assigned value.

ibmappnNodeLsEffCap.name: ibmappnNodeLsEffCap
ibmappnNodeLsEffCap.description: The effective capacity is an integer value that indicates the kilo bits per second. It is derived from the link bandwidth and maximum load factor with the range of 0 thru 603,979,776. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsConnCost.name: ibmappnNodeLsConnCost
ibmappnNodeLsConnCost.description: Cost per connect time: a value representing the relative cost per unit of time to use the TG. Range is from 0, which means no cost, to 255, which indicates maximum cost. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsByteCost.name: ibmappnNodeLsByteCost
ibmappnNodeLsByteCost.description: Relative cost of transmitting a byte over this link. Range is from 0 (lowest cost) to 255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsSecurity.name: ibmappnNodeLsSecurity
ibmappnNodeLsSecurity.description: The security is represented as an integer with a range of 1 thru 255 with the most common values enumerated as defined above. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsDelay
ibmappnNodeLsDelay.description: Relative amount of time that it takes for a signal to travel the length of the logical link. This time is represented in micro seconds, with some of the more common values enumerated. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsUsr1.name: ibmappnNodeLsUsr1
ibmappnNodeLsUsr1.description: First user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsUsr2.name: ibmappnNodeLsUsr2
ibmappnNodeLsUsr2.description: Second user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsUsr3.name: ibmappnNodeLsUsr3
ibmappnNodeLsUsr3.description: Third user-defined TG characteristic for this TG with a range of 0-255. This is an administratively assigned value associated with the TG using this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsEchoRsps.name: ibmappnNodeLsEchoRsps
ibmappnNodeLsEchoRsps.description: Number of responses returned from adjacent link station. A response should be returned for each test frame sent by this node. Test frames are sent to adjacent nodes periodically to verify connectivity and to measure that actual round trip time, that is the time the test frame is sent until the response is received.

ibmappnNodeLsCurrentDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsCurrentDelay
ibmappnNodeLsCurrentDelay.description: The time that it took for the last test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds.

ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelay
ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelay.description: The longest time it took for a test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds .

ibmappnNodeLsMinDelay.name: ibmappnNodeLsMinDelay
ibmappnNodeLsMinDelay.description: The shortest time it took for a test signal to be sent and returned from this link station to the adjacent links station. This time is represented in milliseconds.

ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelayTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelayTime
ibmappnNodeLsMaxDelayTime.description: The time (since system up in hundredth of seconds) when the longest delay occurred. This time can be used to identify when this high water mark occurred in relation to the last initialization of the APPN node.

ibmappnNodeLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodeLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodeLsGoodXids.description: The total number of successful XIDs that have occurred on this link station since the time it was started.

ibmappnNodeLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodeLsBadXids
ibmappnNodeLsBadXids.description: The total number of unsuccessful XIDs that have occurred on this link station since the time it was started.

ibmappnNodeLsSpecific.name: ibmappnNodeLsSpecific
ibmappnNodeLsSpecific.description: Identifies the DLC specific OBJECT IDENTIFIER that can provide additional information.

ibmappnNodeLsStartTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsStartTime
ibmappnNodeLsStartTime.description: The time (in hundredth of seconds) this link station has been active the last time since the time APPN was initialized.

ibmappnNodeLsActiveTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsActiveTime
ibmappnNodeLsActiveTime.description: The time (in hundredth of seconds) this link station has been in the active state. A zero value indicates the link station has never been active.

ibmappnNodeLsCurrentStateTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsCurrentStateTime
ibmappnNodeLsCurrentStateTime.description: The time (in hundredth of seconds) the link station is in the current state.

ibmappnNodeLsIpEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsIpEntry
ibmappnNodeLsIpEntry.description: The IP Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodeLsIpName.name: ibmappnNodeLsIpName
ibmappnNodeLsIpName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsLocalIpPortNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsLocalIpPortNum
ibmappnNodeLsLocalIpPortNum.description: Local TCP/IP port number. The default listening port will be administratively assigned and will dynamically change if this node initiates a session with adjacent node.

ibmappnNodeLsDlsEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsDlsEntry
ibmappnNodeLsDlsEntry.description: The DLS Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodeLsDlsName.name: ibmappnNodeLsDlsName
ibmappnNodeLsDlsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsTrEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsTrEntry
ibmappnNodeLsTrEntry.description: The TR Name is used as the index to this table.

ibmappnNodeLsTrName.name: ibmappnNodeLsTrName
ibmappnNodeLsTrName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station. The name can be from one to eight characters.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusTable.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusTable
ibmappnNodeLsStatusTable.description: This table contains information related to exceptional and potential exceptional conditions that occur during the activation, XID exchange, and termination of the connection.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusEntry.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusEntry
ibmappnNodeLsStatusEntry.description: This table is indexed by the LsStatusIndex, which is an integer that is continuously updated until it eventually wraps. This provides the management station the ability to retrieve only the updates to the table by using the standard GET NEXT.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusIndex.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusIndex
ibmappnNodeLsStatusIndex.description: Table index. The value of the index begins at zero and is incremented up to a maximum value of 2**31-1 (2,147,483,647) before wrapping.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusTime.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusTime
ibmappnNodeLsStatusTime.description: Time (in hundreds of a second) since this node was last initialized.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusLsName.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusLsName
ibmappnNodeLsStatusLsName.description: Administratively-assigned name for this link station.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusCpName.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusCpName
ibmappnNodeLsStatusCpName.description: Administratively-assigned fully-qualified name of the adjacent node partner. This will be provided when the adjacent node has been defined at this node or when the XID sequence has proceeded far enough to to identify the adjacent node. A blank CP name will indicate the name is unknown.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusTgNum.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusTgNum
ibmappnNodeLsStatusTgNum.description: Number associated with the TG to this link station with a range from 0 to 256. A value of 256 indicates the tg number has not been negotiated and is unknown at this time.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusGeneralSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusGeneralSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusGeneralSense.description: The error sense code associated with the start sequence of activation of a link up to the beginning of the XID sequence.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusNofRetry.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusNofRetry
ibmappnNodeLsStatusNofRetry.description: Indicates whether NOF will retry the start request to activate the link.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusEndSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusEndSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusEndSense.description: The sense code associated with the termination of the link connection to adjacent node. This includes all sense information included in the disconnect recieved from the lower layer DLCs and also sense information indicating the link termination originated by upper layer APPN components.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidLocalSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidLocalSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidLocalSense.description: The error sense code associated with the rejection of the XID.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidRemoteSense.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidRemoteSense
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidRemoteSense.description: The error sense code adjacent node returned to this node indicating the reason the XID was rejected.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidByteInError.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidByteInError
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidByteInError.description: This identifies the actual byte in the XID that caused the error. The value of zero (0) indicates that the variable has no meaning.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidBitInError.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidBitInError
ibmappnNodeLsStatusXidBitInError.description: This identifies the actual bit within the error byte of the XID. This only has meaning when the byte in error is greater than zero.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusDlcType.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusDlcType
ibmappnNodeLsStatusDlcType.description: This identifies DLC type that was being used when error occurred. This also is used to the format of the local and remote address provided. other = free form DisplayString ip = ld.ld.ld.ld/2d tr = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx dlsw = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx ethernet = lx:lx:lx:lx:lx:lx.lx

ibmappnNodeLsStatusLocalAddr.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusLocalAddr
ibmappnNodeLsStatusLocalAddr.description: This contains a displayable string that identifies the DLC type and appropriate address. See DlcType above for details of the format.

ibmappnNodeLsStatusRemoteAddr.name: ibmappnNodeLsStatusRemoteAddr
ibmappnNodeLsStatusRemoteAddr.description: This contains a displayable string that identifies the DLC type and appropriate address. See DlcType above for details of the format.

ibmappnSnmpInPkts.name: ibmappnSnmpInPkts
ibmappnSnmpInPkts.description: Total number of messages delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetRequests.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetRequests
ibmappnSnmpInGetRequests.description: Total number of GET requests delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetNexts.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetNexts
ibmappnSnmpInGetNexts.description: Total number of GETNEXT requests delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInSetRequests.name: ibmappnSnmpInSetRequests
ibmappnSnmpInSetRequests.description: Total number of SET requests delivered to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInTotalVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInTotalVars
ibmappnSnmpInTotalVars.description: Total number of VARIABLES included in both GET and GETNEXT requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetVars
ibmappnSnmpInGetVars.description: Total number of VARIBLES included in all GET requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInGetNextVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInGetNextVars
ibmappnSnmpInGetNextVars.description: Total number of VARIABLES included in all GETNEXT requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpInSetVars.name: ibmappnSnmpInSetVars
ibmappnSnmpInSetVars.description: Total number of VARIBLES included in all SET requests to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpOutNoSuchNames.name: ibmappnSnmpOutNoSuchNames
ibmappnSnmpOutNoSuchNames.description: Total number of VARIABLES that could not be found by the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnSnmpOutGenErrs.name: ibmappnSnmpOutGenErrs
ibmappnSnmpOutGenErrs.description: Total number of undefined errors that occurred processing SNMP request to the APPN SNMP sub-agent.

ibmappnMemorySize.name: ibmappnMemorySize
ibmappnMemorySize.description: Size of the shared storage segment, as obtained by storage management from the underlying operating system.

ibmappnMemoryUsed.name: ibmappnMemoryUsed
ibmappnMemoryUsed.description: Number of bytes in the segment that are currently allocated to process.

ibmappnMemoryWarnThresh.name: ibmappnMemoryWarnThresh
ibmappnMemoryWarnThresh.description: Allocation threshold beyond which storage management considers the storage resources to be constrained.

ibmappnMemoryCritThresh.name: ibmappnMemoryCritThresh
ibmappnMemoryCritThresh.description: Allocation threshold beyond which storage management considers the storage resources to be critically constrained.

ibmappnNodeDefLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodeDefLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodeDefLsGoodXids.description: The current number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeDefLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodeDefLsBadXids
ibmappnNodeDefLsBadXids.description: The current number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all defined link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeDynLsGoodXids.name: ibmappnNodeDynLsGoodXids
ibmappnNodeDynLsGoodXids.description: The current number of successfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNodeDynLsBadXids.name: ibmappnNodeDynLsBadXids
ibmappnNodeDynLsBadXids.description: The current number of unsuccessfull XIDs that have occurred on all dynamic link stations since the last time this node was initialized.

ibmappnNnTopoMaxNodes.name: ibmappnNnTopoMaxNodes
ibmappnNnTopoMaxNodes.description: Maximum number of nodes allowed in the APPN topology database This administratively assigned value must be equal to or greater than the maximum total number of end nodes and network nodes. If the number of nodes exceeds this value, APPN will issue an Alert and the node can no longer participate as a network node.

ibmappnNnTopoCurNumNodes.name: ibmappnNnTopoCurNumNodes
ibmappnNnTopoCurNumNodes.description: Current number of nodes in this node's topology database. If this value exceeds the maximum number of nodes allowed (NnTopoMaxNodes), APPN alert CPDB002 is issued.

ibmappnNnTopoInTdus.name: ibmappnNnTopoInTdus
ibmappnNnTopoInTdus.description: Total number of TDUs received from all adjacent NN since last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoOutTdus.name: ibmappnNnTopoOutTdus
ibmappnNnTopoOutTdus.description: Total number of TDUs built by this node to be sent to all adjacent NN since last initialization.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeLowRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeLowRsns
ibmappnNnTopoNodeLowRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN less than the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count. These TDUs are not errors, but result when TDUs are broadcast to all adjacent network nodes. No update to this node's topology database occurs, but this node will send a TDU with it's higher RSN to the adjacent node that sent this low RSN.

ibmappnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns.name: ibmappnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns
ibmappnNnTopoNodeEqualRsns.description: Total number of topology node updates received by this node with a RSN equal to the current RSN. Both even and odd RSN are included in this count.
