ibmappnCosTgRowUsr3Max.description: Maximum acceptable value for this user defined characteristic. Range of values is 0-255.

ibmappnIsInGlobeStatus.name: ibmappnIsInGlobeStatus
ibmappnIsInGlobeStatus.description: Indicates the current collection options in effect: 1. notActive: collection of counters and some names is not active. 2. active: collection of counters and some names is active.

ibmappnIsInGlobeRscv.name: ibmappnIsInGlobeRscv
ibmappnIsInGlobeRscv.description: Indicates the current collection options in effect: 1. notActive: collection of route selection control vectors is not active. 2. active: collection of route selection control vectors is active.

ibmappnIsInGlobeRscvTime.name: ibmappnIsInGlobeRscvTime
ibmappnIsInGlobeRscvTime.description: Time when the ibmappnIsInGlobeRscv object last changed. This time is in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatus.name: ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatus
ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatus.description: Indicates whether or not the intermediate session counters are active. This object reflects the combination of the ibmappnIsInGlobeStatus object and the ibmappnIsAcBtypeActive object. The values are: 1. notActive: collection of counters and some names is not active. 2. active: collection of counters and some names is active.

ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatusTime.name: ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatusTime
ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatusTime.description: Time when the ibmappnIsInGlobeCtrStatus object last changed. This time is in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsInEntry.name: ibmappnIsInEntry
ibmappnIsInEntry.description: Entry of Intermediate Session Information Table.

ibmappnIsInFqLuName.name: ibmappnIsInFqLuName
ibmappnIsInFqLuName.description: The network-qualified CP name or PU name of the node at which the session and cid originated. For APPN and LEN nodes, this is either CP name of the APPN node at which the origin LU is located or the CP name of the NN serving the LEN node at which the origin LU is located. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappnIsInPcid.name: ibmappnIsInPcid
ibmappnIsInPcid.description: The procedure correlation identifier (pcid) of a session. It is an 8-octet value assigned by the primary LU.

ibmappnIsInPriLuName.name: ibmappnIsInPriLuName
ibmappnIsInPriLuName.description: The primary LU name of the session.

ibmappnIsInSecLuName.name: ibmappnIsInSecLuName
ibmappnIsInSecLuName.description: The secondary LU name of the session.

ibmappnIsInModeName.name: ibmappnIsInModeName
ibmappnIsInModeName.description: The Mode Name name used for this session. This is a 1-8 character name.

ibmappnIsInCosName.name: ibmappnIsInCosName
ibmappnIsInCosName.description: The Class of Service (COS) name used for this session. This is a 1-8 character name.

ibmappnIsInTransPriority.name: ibmappnIsInTransPriority
ibmappnIsInTransPriority.description: The transmission priority of this session.

ibmappnIsInSessState.name: ibmappnIsInSessState
ibmappnIsInSessState.description: Indicates the state of the session. 1. session is pending inactive or, 2. session is pending active or, 3. session is active or, 4. session is inactive Existing sessions can be deactivated by setting this object to inactive.

ibmappnIsInSessStartTime.name: ibmappnIsInSessStartTime
ibmappnIsInSessStartTime.description: Time when the session started in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsInSessUpTime.name: ibmappnIsInSessUpTime
ibmappnIsInSessUpTime.description: Length of time the session has been active in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsInCtrUpTime.name: ibmappnIsInCtrUpTime
ibmappnIsInCtrUpTime.description: Length of time the session counters have been active in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsInP2SFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsInP2SFmdPius
ibmappnIsInP2SFmdPius.description: Number of FMD PIUs sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappnIsInS2PFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsInS2PFmdPius
ibmappnIsInS2PFmdPius.description: Number of FMD PIUs sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappnIsInP2SNonFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsInP2SNonFmdPius
ibmappnIsInP2SNonFmdPius.description: Number of non-FMD PIUs sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappnIsInS2PNonFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsInS2PNonFmdPius
ibmappnIsInS2PNonFmdPius.description: Number of non-FMD PIUs sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappnIsInP2SFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsInP2SFmdBytes
ibmappnIsInP2SFmdBytes.description: Number of FMD Bytes sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappnIsInS2PFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsInS2PFmdBytes
ibmappnIsInS2PFmdBytes.description: Number of FMD Bytes sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappnIsInP2SNonFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsInP2SNonFmdBytes
ibmappnIsInP2SNonFmdBytes.description: Number of non-FMD Bytes sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappnIsInS2PNonFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsInS2PNonFmdBytes
ibmappnIsInS2PNonFmdBytes.description: Number of non-FMD Bytes sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappnIsInPsAdjCpName.name: ibmappnIsInPsAdjCpName
ibmappnIsInPsAdjCpName.description: The primary stage adjacent CP name of this session.

ibmappnIsInPsAdjTgNum.name: ibmappnIsInPsAdjTgNum
ibmappnIsInPsAdjTgNum.description: The primary stage adjacent transmission group (TG) number associated with this session.

ibmappnIsInPsSendMaxBtuSize.name: ibmappnIsInPsSendMaxBtuSize
ibmappnIsInPsSendMaxBtuSize.description: The primary stage maximum basic transmission size (BTU) for sending data.

ibmappnIsInPsSendPacingType.name: ibmappnIsInPsSendPacingType
ibmappnIsInPsSendPacingType.description: The primary stage type of pacing being used for sending data.

ibmappnIsInPsSendRpc.name: ibmappnIsInPsSendRpc
ibmappnIsInPsSendRpc.description: The primary stage send residual pace count. This represents the primary stage number of MU's that can still be sent in the current session window.

ibmappnIsInPsSendNxWndwSize.name: ibmappnIsInPsSendNxWndwSize
ibmappnIsInPsSendNxWndwSize.description: The primary stage size of the next window which will be used to send data.

ibmappnIsInPsRecvPacingType.name: ibmappnIsInPsRecvPacingType
ibmappnIsInPsRecvPacingType.description: The primary stage type of pacing being used for receiving data.

ibmappnIsInPsRecvRpc.name: ibmappnIsInPsRecvRpc
ibmappnIsInPsRecvRpc.description: The primary stage receive residual pace count. This represents the primary stage number of MU's that can still be received in the current session window.

ibmappnIsInPsRecvNxWndwSize.name: ibmappnIsInPsRecvNxWndwSize
ibmappnIsInPsRecvNxWndwSize.description: The primary stage size of the next window which will be used to receive data.

ibmappnIsInSsAdjCpName.name: ibmappnIsInSsAdjCpName
ibmappnIsInSsAdjCpName.description: The secondary stage adjacent CP name of this session.

ibmappnIsInSsAdjTgNum.name: ibmappnIsInSsAdjTgNum
ibmappnIsInSsAdjTgNum.description: The secondary stage adjacent transmission group (TG) number associated with this session.

ibmappnIsInSsSendMaxBtuSize.name: ibmappnIsInSsSendMaxBtuSize
ibmappnIsInSsSendMaxBtuSize.description: The secondary stage maximum basic transmission size (BTU) for sending data.

ibmappnIsInSsSendPacingType.name: ibmappnIsInSsSendPacingType
ibmappnIsInSsSendPacingType.description: The secondary stage type of pacing being used for sending data.

ibmappnIsInSsSendRpc.name: ibmappnIsInSsSendRpc
ibmappnIsInSsSendRpc.description: The secondary stage send residual pace count. This represents the secondary stage number of MU's that can still be sent in the current session window.

ibmappnIsInSsSendNxWndwSize.name: ibmappnIsInSsSendNxWndwSize
ibmappnIsInSsSendNxWndwSize.description: The secondary stage size of the next window which will be used to send data.

ibmappnIsInSsRecvPacingType.name: ibmappnIsInSsRecvPacingType
ibmappnIsInSsRecvPacingType.description: The secondary stage type of pacing being used for receiving data.

ibmappnIsInSsRecvRpc.name: ibmappnIsInSsRecvRpc
ibmappnIsInSsRecvRpc.description: The secondary stage send residual pace count. This represents the secondary stage number of MU's that can still be received in the current session window.

ibmappnIsInSsRecvNxWndwSize.name: ibmappnIsInSsRecvNxWndwSize
ibmappnIsInSsRecvNxWndwSize.description: The secondary stage size of the next window which will be used to receive data.

ibmappnIsInRouteInfo.name: ibmappnIsInRouteInfo
ibmappnIsInRouteInfo.description: The route selection control vector (RSCV x'2B') used for this session. It is present for APPN nodes; but is not present for LEN nodes. The format of this vector is described in SNA Formats.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeStatus.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeStatus
ibmappnIsAcGlobeStatus.description: This object indicates the current status for accounting type. 1. indicates collection is not active for any media type. 2. indicates collection is active for at least one media type; and that media is not full. 3. indicates collection is active for at least one media type; but all active medias are full.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeByteThresh.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeByteThresh
ibmappnIsAcGlobeByteThresh.description: The byte threshold for recording accounting information for an active session. If the total of the byte counters (FmdBytes and NonFmdBtyes) is an even multiple of this non-zero value, statistics for this session will be recorded to all active buffers. A value of zero indicates that no byte threshold has been set.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeCheckPt.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeCheckPt
ibmappnIsAcGlobeCheckPt.description: By setting this value to yes, the agent will collect accounting information for all active sessions. This information will be recorded to all active buffers.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcSecs.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcSecs
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcSecs.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) seconds. It contains an integer from 0 to 59. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMins.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMins
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMins.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) minutes. It contains an integer from 0 to 59. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcHours.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcHours
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcHours.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) hours. It contains an integer from 0 to 23. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMdays.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMdays
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMdays.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) day of the month. It contains an integer from 1 to 31; or 0 if the manager has not set this object. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMonths.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMonths
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcMonths.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) months since January. It contains an integer from 0 to 11. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcYears.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcYears
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcYears.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) years since 1900. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcWdays.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcWdays
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcWdays.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) days since Sunday. It contains an integer from 0 to 6. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcYdays.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcYdays
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcYdays.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) days since January 1. It contains an integer from 0 to 365. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcIsdst.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcIsdst
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrUtcIsdst.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) daylight saving time flag. It is positive if daylight saving time is in effect. It is zero if daylight saving time is not in effect. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrName.name: ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrName
ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgrName.description: The name of the manager who set the manager UTC times or NULL if the manager name has not been set. It contains: a. the network id of the manager, b. a period (.) c. the cp name of the manager. By setting this value, the agent will create time record with its corresponding time and name. When setting this object, the manager should also set all other ibmappnIsAcGlobeMgr objects with the same SET operation.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeTable.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeTable
ibmappnIsAcBtypeTable.description: Intermediate Session Accounting Buffer Type Table

ibmappnIsAcBtypeEntry.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeEntry
ibmappnIsAcBtypeEntry.description: Entry of Intermediate Session Accounting Buffer Type Table.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeMedia.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeMedia
ibmappnIsAcBtypeMedia.description: The media for storing the intermediate session accounting records.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeActive.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeActive
ibmappnIsAcBtypeActive.description: Indicates whether or not the buffer media is active. 1. no: indicates the buffer media is not currently used for recording. 2. yes: indicates the buffer media is currently being used for recording.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeDirName.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeDirName
ibmappnIsAcBtypeDirName.description: The name of the directory which will be used to allocate and write buffers of this type. For memory buffer types, this field will be NULL.

ibmappnIsAcBtypePrdMaxBufs.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypePrdMaxBufs
ibmappnIsAcBtypePrdMaxBufs.description: The maximum number of buffer medias supported by the product.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeMaxBufs.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeMaxBufs
ibmappnIsAcBtypeMaxBufs.description: The maximum number of buffer medias which will be used for recording accounting information. This value must be in the range of zero to the Product Maximum.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeCurBufs.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeCurBufs
ibmappnIsAcBtypeCurBufs.description: The current number of buffer media. This is the sum of all full and in use buffers of this type.

ibmappnIsAcBtypePrdRecPerBuf.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypePrdRecPerBuf
ibmappnIsAcBtypePrdRecPerBuf.description: The maximum number of records supported by the product.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeRecPerBuf.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeRecPerBuf
ibmappnIsAcBtypeRecPerBuf.description: The maximum number of records which will be recorded in an individual buffer. This value must be in the range of zero to the Product Maximum.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeRecFormat.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeRecFormat
ibmappnIsAcBtypeRecFormat.description: This defines the recording format of records. (1) ascii: records are recorded in ascii (english text format) (2) binary: records are recorded in binary (machine readable format)

ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullAction.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullAction
ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullAction.description: This defines the behaviour used when all buffer medias are full. (1) halt: stop creating new records (2) wrap: overwrite the existing records.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullTime.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullTime
ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullTime.description: The time which the full condition was encountered. This time is represented in hundreds of a second since the node was started. 2**32-1 (4,294,967,295), and wraps.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullReason.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullReason
ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullReason.description: The reason the buffer media is full. (1) The media is not full. (2) The maximum number of buffers have been reach, all buffers are full and the full action is halt. (3) The maximum number of buffers is zero or the maximum number of records is less than 5 or a unique record number cannot be generated. (4) Unable to write to the media due to I/O errors.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullWraps.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullWraps
ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullWraps.description: The number of accounting records being overwritten due to buffer full situation.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullLosts.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullLosts
ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullLosts.description: The number of new accounting records lost due to the buffer full situation.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorWraps.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorWraps
ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorWraps.description: The number of accounting records lost to due to other reasons, (e.g. I/O error, software error) while in a wrap condition.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorLosts.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorLosts
ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorLosts.description: The number of accounting records lost to due to other reasons, (e.g. I/O error, software error) while not in a full condition.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeCheckPts.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeCheckPts
ibmappnIsAcBtypeCheckPts.description: The number of times a buffer of this type has been recorded to for checkpointing active intermediate sessions.

ibmappnIsAcBtypePurges.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypePurges
ibmappnIsAcBtypePurges.description: The number of times a buffer of this type has been purged.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeDeletes.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeDeletes
ibmappnIsAcBtypeDeletes.description: The number of times an entry has been deleted from a buffer of this type.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeResets.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeResets
ibmappnIsAcBtypeResets.description: The number of times the Btype counters have been reset as a result of a SET.

ibmappnIsAcBtypeClearStats.name: ibmappnIsAcBtypeClearStats
ibmappnIsAcBtypeClearStats.description: By setting this object to yes, all statistics for this media type will be cleared (set to zero); and the Btype reset counter will be incremented. Objects affected by this include: - ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullTime - ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullReason - ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullWraps - ibmappnIsAcBtypeFullLosts - ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorWraps - ibmappnIsAcBtypeErrorLosts - ibmappnIsAcBtypeCheckPts - ibmappnIsAcBtypePurges - ibmappnIsAcBtypeDeletes

ibmappnIsAcBufEntry.name: ibmappnIsAcBufEntry
ibmappnIsAcBufEntry.description: Entry of Intermediate Session Accounting Buffer Table.

ibmappnIsAcBufMedia.name: ibmappnIsAcBufMedia
ibmappnIsAcBufMedia.description: The media for storing the intermediate session accounting records.

ibmappnIsAcBufNumber.name: ibmappnIsAcBufNumber
ibmappnIsAcBufNumber.description: Number of the buffer. Each time a new buffer is used for recording, an incremented number will be assigned. Thus, the order of in which the buffers filled can be determined.

ibmappnIsAcBufState.name: ibmappnIsAcBufState
ibmappnIsAcBufState.description: The current buffer state. 1. complete: indicates the buffer is full or recording is not active for this buffer. In either case, the buffer is ready to be retrieved. This value may be specified in a SET operation to change a buffers state from active to complete. 2. active: indicates the buffer is currently being used for recording. This value is not valid for use in a SET operation. 3. purge: indicates the buffer should be purged. This value may be specified in a SET operation to remove a buffer. Specification of this value is only valid for complete buffers. It is not valid for active buffers.

ibmappnIsAcBufRecFormat.name: ibmappnIsAcBufRecFormat
ibmappnIsAcBufRecFormat.description: This defines the recording format of records. (1) ascii: records are recorded in ascii (english text format) (2) binary: records are recorded in binary (machine readable format)

ibmappnIsAcBufMaxRecords.name: ibmappnIsAcBufMaxRecords
ibmappnIsAcBufMaxRecords.description: The maximum number of records this buffer may contain. It is derived from the number of records per buffer set in the buffer type table.

ibmappnIsAcBufOldestIndex.name: ibmappnIsAcBufOldestIndex
ibmappnIsAcBufOldestIndex.description: The oldest accounting index contained in this buffer. By setting this object, all records with indexes less than this value will be deleted. The set value must be greater than or equal to the current oldest index and less than or equal to the current newest index. Setting of this object will not be honored for all types of buffers.

ibmappnIsAcBufNewestIndex.name: ibmappnIsAcBufNewestIndex
ibmappnIsAcBufNewestIndex.description: The newest accounting index contained in this buffer.

ibmappnIsAcTimeEntry.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeEntry
ibmappnIsAcTimeEntry.description: Entry of Intermediate Session Accounting Time Table.

ibmappnIsAcTimeIndex.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeIndex
ibmappnIsAcTimeIndex.description: Intermediate Session Time record index. It starts with 0, and increase up to maximum value of 2**31-1 (2,147,483,647), and wraps.

ibmappnIsAcTimeEntryType.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeEntryType
ibmappnIsAcTimeEntryType.description: Indicates whether the entry was made as the result of: 1. a SET to start collecting accounting data, or 2. a SET to stop collecting accounting data, or 3. the creation of a new media to store accounting data, or 4. a media was full and wrapped (over writing records), or 5. the system time changed, or 6. a manager set the manager times and/or manager name, or 7. the record format for this media changed, or 8. time reference for the media

ibmappnIsAcTimeForMedia.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeForMedia
ibmappnIsAcTimeForMedia.description: This object qualifies the time entry type. It indicates the media type for which the entry occured.

ibmappnIsAcTimeRecTime.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeRecTime
ibmappnIsAcTimeRecTime.description: Intermediate Session Record time. It represents the time in hundreds of a second since the node was started. 2**32-1 (4,294,967,295), and wraps.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcSecs.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcSecs
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcSecs.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) seconds. It contains an integer from 0 to 59.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMins.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMins
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMins.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) minutes. It contains an integer from 0 to 59.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcHours.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcHours
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcHours.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) hours. It contains an integer from 0 to 23.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMdays.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMdays
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMdays.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) day of the month. It contains an integer from 1 to 31.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMonths.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMonths
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcMonths.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) months since January. It contains an integer from 0 to 11.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcYears.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcYears
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcYears.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) years since 1900.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcWdays.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcWdays
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcWdays.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) days since Sunday. It contains an integer from 0 to 6.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcYdays.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcYdays
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcYdays.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) days since January 1. It contains an integer from 0 to 365.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcIsdst.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcIsdst
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtUtcIsdst.description: The agents Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) daylight saving time flag. It is positive if daylight saving time is in effect. It is zero if daylight saving time is not in effect.

ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtName.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtName
ibmappnIsAcTimeAgtName.description: The name of the agent who set the agent UTC times. It contains: a. the network id of the agent, b. a period (.) c. the cp name of the agent.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcSecs.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcSecs
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcSecs.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) seconds. It contains an integer from 0 to 59.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMins.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMins
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMins.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) minutes. It contains an integer from 0 to 59.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcHours.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcHours
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcHours.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) hours. It contains an integer from 0 to 23.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMdays.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMdays
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMdays.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) day of the month. It contains an integer from 1 to 31; or 0 if the manager has not set this object.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMonths.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMonths
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcMonths.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) months since January. It contains an integer from 0 to 11.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcYears.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcYears
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcYears.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) years since 1900.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcWdays.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcWdays
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcWdays.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) days since Sunday. It contains an integer from 0 to 6.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcYdays.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcYdays
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcYdays.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) days since January 1. It contains an integer from 0 to 365.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcIsdst.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcIsdst
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrUtcIsdst.description: The managers Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) daylight saving time flag. It is positive if daylight saving time is in effect. It is zero if daylight saving time is not in effect.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrName.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrName
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrName.description: The name of the manager who set the manager UTC times or NULL if the manager name has not been set. It contains: a. the network id of the manager, b. a period (.) c. the cp name of the manager.

ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrTimeValid.name: ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrTimeValid
ibmappnIsAcTimeMgrTimeValid.description: This indicates whether or not the the manager UTC times are valid. It is set by the manager if the manager determines the manager UTC times are valid.

ibmappnIsAcDataEntry.name: ibmappnIsAcDataEntry
ibmappnIsAcDataEntry.description: Entry of Intermediate Session Accounting Data Table.

ibmappnIsAcIndex.name: ibmappnIsAcIndex
ibmappnIsAcIndex.description: Session accounting record index. Upon initial startup, it will begin with 0, and increase up to maximum value of 2**31-1 (2,147,483,647), and wraps. Upon subsequent startups, it will be initialized with the value of the oldest index in any media type; or 0 if no indices are found.

ibmappnIsAcEntryType.name: ibmappnIsAcEntryType
ibmappnIsAcEntryType.description: Indicates whether the entry was made as the result of: 1. a session starting or, 2. a session ending or, 3. a session threshold reached or 4. a session checkpoint request

ibmappnIsAcRecTime.name: ibmappnIsAcRecTime
ibmappnIsAcRecTime.description: Intermediate Session Record time. It represents the time in hundreds of a second since the node was started. 2**32-1 (4,294,967,295), and wraps.

ibmappnIsAcFqLuName.name: ibmappnIsAcFqLuName
ibmappnIsAcFqLuName.description: The network-qualified CP name or PU name of the node at which the session and pcid originated. For APPN and LEN nodes, this is either CP name of the APPN node at which the origin LU is located or the CP name of the NN serving the LEN node at which the origin LU is located. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappnIsAcPcid.name: ibmappnIsAcPcid
ibmappnIsAcPcid.description: The procedure correlation identifier (pcid) of a session. It is an 8-octet value assigned by the primary LU.

ibmappnIsAcPriLuName.name: ibmappnIsAcPriLuName
ibmappnIsAcPriLuName.description: Primary LU Name of the session.

ibmappnIsAcSecLuName.name: ibmappnIsAcSecLuName
ibmappnIsAcSecLuName.description: Secondary LU Name of the session.

ibmappnIsAcModeName.name: ibmappnIsAcModeName
ibmappnIsAcModeName.description: The mode name used for this session

ibmappnIsAcCosName.name: ibmappnIsAcCosName
ibmappnIsAcCosName.description: The class of service (cos) used for this session

ibmappnIsAcTransPriority.name: ibmappnIsAcTransPriority
ibmappnIsAcTransPriority.description: Transmission priority for this session. The values are: 1. Low 2. Medium 3. High 4. Network

ibmappnIsAcSessState.name: ibmappnIsAcSessState
ibmappnIsAcSessState.description: Indicates the state of the session. 1. session is pending inactive or, 2. session is pending active or, 3. session is active or, 4. session is inactive

ibmappnIsAcSessStartTime.name: ibmappnIsAcSessStartTime
ibmappnIsAcSessStartTime.description: Time when the session started in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsAcSessUpTime.name: ibmappnIsAcSessUpTime
ibmappnIsAcSessUpTime.description: Length of time the session has been active in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsAcCtrUpTime.name: ibmappnIsAcCtrUpTime
ibmappnIsAcCtrUpTime.description: Length of time the session counters have been active in hundreds of a second.

ibmappnIsAcEndReason.name: ibmappnIsAcEndReason
ibmappnIsAcEndReason.description: The SNA sense code which resulted when the session ended.

ibmappnIsAcP2SFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsAcP2SFmdPius
ibmappnIsAcP2SFmdPius.description: The number of FMD PIU's sent from the primary LU to the secondary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcS2PFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsAcS2PFmdPius
ibmappnIsAcS2PFmdPius.description: The number of FMD PIU's sent from the secondary LU to the primary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcP2SNonFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsAcP2SNonFmdPius
ibmappnIsAcP2SNonFmdPius.description: The number of non-FMD PIU's sent from the primary LU to the secondary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcS2PNonFmdPius.name: ibmappnIsAcS2PNonFmdPius
ibmappnIsAcS2PNonFmdPius.description: The number of non-FMD PIU's sent from the secondary LU to the primary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcP2SFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsAcP2SFmdBytes
ibmappnIsAcP2SFmdBytes.description: The number of FMD bytes sent from the primary LU to the secondary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcS2PFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsAcS2PFmdBytes
ibmappnIsAcS2PFmdBytes.description: The number of FMD bytes sent from the secondary LU to the primary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcP2SNonFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsAcP2SNonFmdBytes
ibmappnIsAcP2SNonFmdBytes.description: The number of non-FMD bytes sent from the primary LU to the secondary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcS2PNonFmdBytes.name: ibmappnIsAcS2PNonFmdBytes
ibmappnIsAcS2PNonFmdBytes.description: The number of non-FMD bytes sent from the secondary LU to the primary LU. The counter has a range of of 0 to 2**32; and then wraps.

ibmappnIsAcRouteInfo.name: ibmappnIsAcRouteInfo
ibmappnIsAcRouteInfo.description: The route selection control vector (RSCV x'2B') used for this session. It is present for APPN nodes; but is not present for LEN nodes.

ibmappcInGlobeStatus.name: ibmappcInGlobeStatus
ibmappcInGlobeStatus.description: Indicates the current collection options in effect: 1. notActive: collection of counters and some names is not active. 2. active: collection of counters and some names is active.

ibmappcInGlobeRscv.name: ibmappcInGlobeRscv
ibmappcInGlobeRscv.description: Indicates the current collection options in effect: 1. notActive: collection of route selection control vectors is not active. 2. active: collection of route selection control vectors is active.

ibmappcInGlobeRscvTime.name: ibmappcInGlobeRscvTime
ibmappcInGlobeRscvTime.description: Time when the ibmappcInGlobeRscv object last changed. This time is in hundreds of a second.

ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatus.name: ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatus
ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatus.description: Indicates whether or not the appc session counters are active. This object reflects the combination of the ibmappcInGlobeStatus object and any other product dependant object(s). The values are: 1. notActive: collection of counters and some names is not active. 2. active: collection of counters and some names is active.

ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatusTime.name: ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatusTime
ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatusTime.description: Time when the ibmappcInGlobeCtrStatus object last changed. This time is in hundreds of a second.

ibmappcInGlobeActSess.name: ibmappcInGlobeActSess
ibmappcInGlobeActSess.description: Number of currently active APPC sessions

ibmappcInLluEntry.name: ibmappcInLluEntry
ibmappcInLluEntry.description: Entry of APPC Local Lu Information Table.

ibmappcInLluLuName.name: ibmappcInLluLuName
ibmappcInLluLuName.description: The network-qualified LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInLluDefType.name: ibmappcInLluDefType
ibmappcInLluDefType.description: Indicates whether the LU definition was specified in the nodes system definitions or was dynamically created.

ibmappcInLluSessLimit.name: ibmappcInLluSessLimit
ibmappcInLluSessLimit.description: The maximum number of session supported by this LU.

ibmappcInLluBindRspMayQ.name: ibmappcInLluBindRspMayQ
ibmappcInLluBindRspMayQ.description: Indicates whether or not a received bind response will be queued if the LU is not currently active.

ibmappcInLluDefaultLu.name: ibmappcInLluDefaultLu
ibmappcInLluDefaultLu.description: Indicates whether the LU is the default LU for the node.

ibmappcInLluCntlPtLu.name: ibmappcInLluCntlPtLu
ibmappcInLluCntlPtLu.description: Indicates whether or not the LU is the control point (CP) LU.

ibmappcInLluCurActSess.name: ibmappcInLluCurActSess
ibmappcInLluCurActSess.description: The number of currently active sessions.

ibmappcInRluEntry.name: ibmappcInRluEntry
ibmappcInRluEntry.description: Entry of APPC Remote Partner Lu Information Table.

ibmappcInRluLocLuName.name: ibmappcInRluLocLuName
ibmappcInRluLocLuName.description: The network-qualified local LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInRluParLuName.name: ibmappcInRluParLuName
ibmappcInRluParLuName.description: The network-qualified partner LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInRluParLuLocName.name: ibmappcInRluParLuLocName
ibmappcInRluParLuLocName.description: The network-qualified partner LU local name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInRluDefType.name: ibmappcInRluDefType
ibmappcInRluDefType.description: Indicates whether the LU definition was specified in the nodes system definitions or was dynamically created.

ibmappcInRluDefParaSessSup.name: ibmappcInRluDefParaSessSup
ibmappcInRluDefParaSessSup.description: Defined Parallel Sessions Supported. Indicates whether or not multiple session between the partner LU and its associated local LU are permitted.

ibmappcInRluDefCnosSup.name: ibmappcInRluDefCnosSup
ibmappcInRluDefCnosSup.description: Defined CNOS Supported. Indicates whether or not Change Number of Sessions (CNOS) will be used to negotiate session limits between the logical points.

ibmappcInRluDefAllVerSup.name: ibmappcInRluDefAllVerSup
ibmappcInRluDefAllVerSup.description: Defined Already Verified Accepted. Indicates whether or not an attach, specifying that TP security has already been verified, is accepted by the adjacent CP LU.

ibmappcInRluDefAttSecSup.name: ibmappcInRluDefAttSecSup
ibmappcInRluDefAttSecSup.description: Defined Attach Security Supported. Indicates whether or not the adjacent CP LU supports attach security.

ibmappcInRluDefSessSecSup.name: ibmappcInRluDefSessSecSup
ibmappcInRluDefSessSecSup.description: Defined Session Security Supported. Indicates whether or not the adjacent CP LU may omit a password in the user data portion of the BIND.

ibmappcInRluDefEnhanSecSup.name: ibmappcInRluDefEnhanSecSup
ibmappcInRluDefEnhanSecSup.description: Defined Enhance Security Supported. Indicates the level of enhance security support: 1 = none 2 = level 1 3 = level 2

ibmappcInRluActType.name: ibmappcInRluActType
ibmappcInRluActType.description: Indicates whether the LU active definitions are currently active or not currently active.

ibmappcInRluActParaSessSup.name: ibmappcInRluActParaSessSup
ibmappcInRluActParaSessSup.description: Active Parallel Sessions Supported. Indicates whether or not multiple session between the partner LU and its associated local LU are permitted.

ibmappcInRluActCnosSup.name: ibmappcInRluActCnosSup
ibmappcInRluActCnosSup.description: Active CNOS Supported. Indicates whether or not Change Number of Sessions (CNOS) will be used to negotiate session limits between the logical points.

ibmappcInRluActAllVerSup.name: ibmappcInRluActAllVerSup
ibmappcInRluActAllVerSup.description: Active Already Verified Accepted. Indicates whether or not an attach, specifying that TP security has already been verified, is accepted by the adjacent CP LU.

ibmappcInRluActAttSecSup.name: ibmappcInRluActAttSecSup
ibmappcInRluActAttSecSup.description: Active Attach Security Supported. Indicates whether or not the adjacent CP LU supports attach security.

ibmappcInRluActSessSecSup.name: ibmappcInRluActSessSecSup
ibmappcInRluActSessSecSup.description: Active Session Security Supported. Indicates whether or not the adjacent CP LU may omit a password in the user data portion of the BIND.

ibmappcInRluActEnhanSecSup.name: ibmappcInRluActEnhanSecSup
ibmappcInRluActEnhanSecSup.description: Active Enhance Security Supported. Indicates the level of enhance security support: 1 = none 2 = level 1 3 = level 2

ibmappcInMdEntry.name: ibmappcInMdEntry
ibmappcInMdEntry.description: Entry of APPC Mode Information Table.

ibmappcInMdLluName.name: ibmappcInMdLluName
ibmappcInMdLluName.description: The network-qualified local LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInMdRluName.name: ibmappcInMdRluName
ibmappcInMdRluName.description: The network-qualified remote LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInMdDefType.name: ibmappcInMdDefType
ibmappcInMdDefType.description: Indicates whether the mode definition was specified in the nodes system definitions or was dynamically created.

ibmappcInMdSessEndTpName.name: ibmappcInMdSessEndTpName
ibmappcInMdSessEndTpName.description: The session end point transaction program name.

ibmappcInMdSessLimit.name: ibmappcInMdSessLimit
ibmappcInMdSessLimit.description: Session Limit. Identifies the total number of sessions that can be established with the partner LU.

ibmappcInMdMaxSessLimit.name: ibmappcInMdMaxSessLimit
ibmappcInMdMaxSessLimit.description: Maximum Session Limit. Specifies the maximum number of sessions supported by the LU pair using this mode name.

ibmappcInMdAutoActLimit.name: ibmappcInMdAutoActLimit
ibmappcInMdAutoActLimit.description: Auto Activate Limit. Specifies the maximum number of sessions which can be activated when this mode is active.

ibmappcInMdDrainSelf.name: ibmappcInMdDrainSelf
ibmappcInMdDrainSelf.description: Drain Self. Indicates whether or not the local LU can be drained.

ibmappcInMdDrainPart.name: ibmappcInMdDrainPart
ibmappcInMdDrainPart.description: Drain Partner. Indicates whether or not the partner LU can be drained.

ibmappcInMdMinCwinLimit.name: ibmappcInMdMinCwinLimit
ibmappcInMdMinCwinLimit.description: Minimum Conwinners Limit. Identifies the minimum number of conwinner sessions.

ibmappcInMdMinClosLimit.name: ibmappcInMdMinClosLimit
ibmappcInMdMinClosLimit.description: Minimum Conlossers Limit. Identifies the minimum number of conloser sessions.

ibmappcInMdRecvPacWinSz.name: ibmappcInMdRecvPacWinSz
ibmappcInMdRecvPacWinSz.description: The size of the receive pacing window.

ibmappcInMdSendPacWinSz.name: ibmappcInMdSendPacWinSz
ibmappcInMdSendPacWinSz.description: The size of the send pacing window.

ibmappcInMdRecvRuSzUpBnd.name: ibmappcInMdRecvRuSzUpBnd
ibmappcInMdRecvRuSzUpBnd.description: The receive ru upper boundary size.

ibmappcInMdSendRuSzUpBnd.name: ibmappcInMdSendRuSzUpBnd
ibmappcInMdSendRuSzUpBnd.description: The send ru upper boundary size.

ibmappcInMdRecvRuSzLoBnd.name: ibmappcInMdRecvRuSzLoBnd
ibmappcInMdRecvRuSzLoBnd.description: The receive ru lower boundary size.

ibmappcInMdSendRuSzLoBnd.name: ibmappcInMdSendRuSzLoBnd
ibmappcInMdSendRuSzLoBnd.description: The send ru lower boundary size.

ibmappcInMdPtmCwin.name: ibmappcInMdPtmCwin
ibmappcInMdPtmCwin.description: The number of pending termination conlosers.

ibmappcInMdPtmClos.name: ibmappcInMdPtmClos
ibmappcInMdPtmClos.description: The number of pending termination conwinners.

ibmappcInMdFreeSessLst.name: ibmappcInMdFreeSessLst
ibmappcInMdFreeSessLst.description: The size of the free seesion list.

ibmappcInMdWaitReqLst.name: ibmappcInMdWaitReqLst
ibmappcInMdWaitReqLst.description: The size of the waiting request list.

ibmappcInLtpEntry.name: ibmappcInLtpEntry
ibmappcInLtpEntry.description: Entry of APPC Local TP Information Table.

ibmappcInLtpLuName.name: ibmappcInLtpLuName
ibmappcInLtpLuName.description: The network-qualified local LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInLtpDefType.name: ibmappcInLtpDefType
ibmappcInLtpDefType.description: The TP definition type. Indicates whether the TP was specified in the nodes system definitions or was dynamically created.

ibmappcInLtpPfCnos.name: ibmappcInLtpPfCnos
ibmappcInLtpPfCnos.description: The TP Change Number of Sessions (CNOS) privileged function. This parameter specifies whether or not this program is allowed to issue CNOS verbs.

ibmappcInLtpPfSessCntl.name: ibmappcInLtpPfSessCntl
ibmappcInLtpPfSessCntl.description: The TP Session Control privileged function. This parameter specifies whether or not this program is allowed to issue ACTIVATE_SESSION and DEACTIVATE_SESSION verbs.

ibmappcInLtpPfDefine.name: ibmappcInLtpPfDefine
ibmappcInLtpPfDefine.description: The TP Define privileged function. This parameter specifies whether or not this program is allowed to issue DEFINE and DELETE verbs.

ibmappcInLtpPfDisplay.name: ibmappcInLtpPfDisplay
ibmappcInLtpPfDisplay.description: The TP Display privileged function. This parameter specifies whether or not this program is allowed to issue DISPLAY verbs.

ibmappcInLtpPfAllocSer.name: ibmappcInLtpPfAllocSer
ibmappcInLtpPfAllocSer.description: The TP Allocate Service privileged function. This parameter specifies whether or not this program is allowed to issue the ALLOCATE verb with its TPN parameter specifying an SNA service transmission program.

ibmappcInLtpRescSup.name: ibmappcInLtpRescSup
ibmappcInLtpRescSup.description: The TP resources supported parameter. 1. basic conversations 2. mapped conversations 3. all conversations

ibmappcInLtpPipSubNum.name: ibmappcInLtpPipSubNum
ibmappcInLtpPipSubNum.description: The TP number of pip subfields.

ibmappcInSsEntry.name: ibmappcInSsEntry
ibmappcInSsEntry.description: Entry of APPC Session Information Table.

ibmappcInSsFqLuName.name: ibmappcInSsFqLuName
ibmappcInSsFqLuName.description: The network-qualified CP name or PU name of the node at which the session and cid originated. For APPN and LEN nodes, this is either CP name of the APPN node at which the origin LU is located or the CP name of the NN serving the LEN node at which the origin LU is located. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInSsPcid.name: ibmappcInSsPcid
ibmappcInSsPcid.description: The procedure correlation identifier (pcid) of a session. It is an 8-octet value assigned by the primary LU.

ibmappcInSsPluName.name: ibmappcInSsPluName
ibmappcInSsPluName.description: The primary LU name of the session.

ibmappcInSsSluName.name: ibmappcInSsSluName
ibmappcInSsSluName.description: The secondary LU name of the session.

ibmappcInSsModeName.name: ibmappcInSsModeName
ibmappcInSsModeName.description: The Mode Name name used for this session. This is a 1-8 character name.

ibmappcInSsCosName.name: ibmappcInSsCosName
ibmappcInSsCosName.description: The Class of Service (COS) name used for this session. This is a 1-8 character name.

ibmappcInSsSessState.name: ibmappcInSsSessState
ibmappcInSsSessState.description: Indicates the state of the session. 1. session is pending inactive or, 2. session is pending active or, 3. session is active or, 4. session is inactive

ibmappcInSsTransPriority.name: ibmappcInSsTransPriority
ibmappcInSsTransPriority.description: The transmission priority of this session.

ibmappcInSsPaceType.name: ibmappcInSsPaceType
ibmappcInSsPaceType.description: The type of pacing used for this session.

ibmappcInSsSendMaxRuSz.name: ibmappcInSsSendMaxRuSz
ibmappcInSsSendMaxRuSz.description: The maximum ru size which can be sent.

ibmappcInSsRecvMaxRuSz.name: ibmappcInSsRecvMaxRuSz
ibmappcInSsRecvMaxRuSz.description: The maximum ru size which can be received.

ibmappcInSsEnhanceSecSup.name: ibmappcInSsEnhanceSecSup
ibmappcInSsEnhanceSecSup.description: Enhanced security supported. Indicates the level of enhance security support: 1 = none 2 = level 1 3 = level 2

ibmappcInSsSendPacingType.name: ibmappcInSsSendPacingType
ibmappcInSsSendPacingType.description: The type of pacing being used for sending data.

ibmappcInSsSendRpc.name: ibmappcInSsSendRpc
ibmappcInSsSendRpc.description: The send residual pace count. This represents the number of MU's that can still be sent in the current session window.

ibmappcInSsSendNxWndwSize.name: ibmappcInSsSendNxWndwSize
ibmappcInSsSendNxWndwSize.description: The size of the next window which will be used to send data.

ibmappcInSsRecvPacingType.name: ibmappcInSsRecvPacingType
ibmappcInSsRecvPacingType.description: The type of pacing being used for receiving data.

ibmappcInSsRecvRpc.name: ibmappcInSsRecvRpc
ibmappcInSsRecvRpc.description: The receive residual pace count. This represents the number of MU's that can still be received in the current session window.

ibmappcInSsRecvNxWndwSize.name: ibmappcInSsRecvNxWndwSize
ibmappcInSsRecvNxWndwSize.description: The size of the next window which will be used to receive data.

ibmappcInSsSessStartTime.name: ibmappcInSsSessStartTime
ibmappcInSsSessStartTime.description: Time when the session started in hundreds of a second.

ibmappcInSsSessUpTime.name: ibmappcInSsSessUpTime
ibmappcInSsSessUpTime.description: Length of time the session has been active in hundreds of a second.

ibmappcInSsCtrUpTime.name: ibmappcInSsCtrUpTime
ibmappcInSsCtrUpTime.description: Length of time the session counters have been active in hundreds of a second.

ibmappcInSsS2PFmdPius.name: ibmappcInSsS2PFmdPius
ibmappcInSsS2PFmdPius.description: Number of FMD PIUs sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappcInSsP2SNonFmdPius.name: ibmappcInSsP2SNonFmdPius
ibmappcInSsP2SNonFmdPius.description: Number of non-FMD PIUs sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappcInSsS2PNonFmdPius.name: ibmappcInSsS2PNonFmdPius
ibmappcInSsS2PNonFmdPius.description: Number of non-FMD PIUs sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappcInSsP2SFmdBytes.name: ibmappcInSsP2SFmdBytes
ibmappcInSsP2SFmdBytes.description: Number of FMD Bytes sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappcInSsS2PFmdBytes.name: ibmappcInSsS2PFmdBytes
ibmappcInSsS2PFmdBytes.description: Number of FMD Bytes sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU

ibmappcInSsP2SNonFmdBytes.name: ibmappcInSsP2SNonFmdBytes
ibmappcInSsP2SNonFmdBytes.description: Number of non-FMD Bytes sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU

ibmappcInSsRscv.name: ibmappcInSsRscv
ibmappcInSsRscv.description: The route selection control vector (RSCV x'2B') used for this session. It is not present for APPN CP-CP sessions and also not present for LEN nodes. The format of this vector is described in SNA Formats.

ibmappcInSsStatusEntry.name: ibmappcInSsStatusEntry
ibmappcInSsStatusEntry.description: Entry of APPC Session Status Information Table. This table is indexed by the SsStatusIndex, which is an integer that is continuously updated until it eventually wraps. This provides the management station the ability to retrieve only the updates to the table by using the standard GET NEXT.

ibmappcInSsStatusIndex.name: ibmappcInSsStatusIndex
ibmappcInSsStatusIndex.description: Table index. The value of the index begins at zero and is incremented up to a maximum value of 2**31-1 (2,147,483,647) before wrapping.

ibmappcInSsStatusTime.name: ibmappcInSsStatusTime
ibmappcInSsStatusTime.description: Time (in hundreds of a second) since this node was last initialized.

ibmappcInSsStatusType.name: ibmappcInSsStatusType
ibmappcInSsStatusType.description: Indicates the entry type: 1. Received a negative bind response from the partner LU. 2. Sent a negative bind response to the partner LU. 3. Session activation rejected by the partner LU. 4. Unbind sent to the partner LU. 5. Unbind received from the partner LU.

ibmappcInSsStatusLocLuName.name: ibmappcInSsStatusLocLuName
ibmappcInSsStatusLocLuName.description: The network-qualified local LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInSsStatusParLuName.name: ibmappcInSsStatusParLuName
ibmappcInSsStatusParLuName.description: The network-qualified partner LU name. This field is from 3 to 17 characters in length, including a period (.) which separates the NetId from the NAU name.

ibmappcInSsStatusUnbindType.name: ibmappcInSsStatusUnbindType
ibmappcInSsStatusUnbindType.description: The type of unbind which terminated the session. This value is consists of one (1) octet; and its meaning is defined in SNA Formats.

ibmappcInSsStatusSenseCode.name: ibmappcInSsStatusSenseCode
ibmappcInSsStatusSenseCode.description: The sense code associated with the termination of the session. This value consists of four (4) octets; and its meaning is defined in SNA Formats.

ibmappcInSsStatusComponentId.name: ibmappcInSsStatusComponentId
ibmappcInSsStatusComponentId.description: The name of the component which sent the entry.

ibmappcInSsStatusDetectModule.name: ibmappcInSsStatusDetectModule
ibmappcInSsStatusDetectModule.description: The name of the module which detected the condition and sent the entry.
